{"type":"message","id":"3941a9d8","parentId":"3e9bd4fc","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:15:00.108Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at the settings data model. The `requiredFields` comes from `settings?.requiredFields`. Let me check if \"tuition\" is in the requiredFields, and also check what \"vui lòng nhập tuition\" error message says.\n\nActually, looking at line 407, `requiredConfig.forEach` iterates over `settings?.requiredFields || []`. The error messages come from the labels map. But `tuition` is not in the labels map, so the error would be \"Vui lòng nhập tuition.\" if `tuition` was in `requiredFields`.\n\nWait, actually the error would be `errs[f] = `Vui lòng ${action} ${labels[f] || f}.`;` where `action = (f === 'rank' || ...) ? 'chọn' : 'nhập'`. \n\nSo if `f = 'tuition'`, it would say \"Vui lòng nhập tuition.\" But the user said \"vui lòng nhập tuition\", which might actually mean the tuition field is being required when it shouldn't be. Let me look at the submit handler around line 820 to see where this error is coming from.","thinkingSignature":"4cee526c0bbd57bd39fb0348ec55e28490b7e655e23c1195aa18771329870390"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o55s3nomaul6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/components/students/StudentDetailDrawer.tsx","offset":800,"limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":265,"output":332,"cacheRead":33828,"cacheWrite":1577,"totalTokens":36002,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776960892729,"responseId":"0639787e5c9e6bde7cf5b26278f07545"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07ebed5d","parentId":"3941a9d8","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:15:00.167Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o55s3nomaul6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                        gender: (form.elements.namedItem('gender') as HTMLSelectElement)?.value,\n                        phone,\n                        identity_number: cccd,\n                        identity_card: cccd, // Standardized for backend compatibility\n                        rank: selectedRank,\n                        license_category_id: selectedRank,\n                        city: selectedCity,\n                        region_id: selectedCity,\n                        address: (form.elements.namedItem('address') as HTMLInputElement)?.value,\n                        course: selectedCourse,\n                        enrollment_date: selectedEnrollmentDate,\n                        referrer: (form.elements.namedItem('referrer') as HTMLInputElement)?.value,\n                        status: (form.elements.namedItem('status') as HTMLSelectElement)?.value,\n                        status_detail: selectedCourse ? 'Đã vào khóa' : 'Chờ KSK',\n                        fee: Number(parseNumberFromDots(currentFee || '0')),\n                        lead_manager: selectedLead || null,\n                        note: (form.elements.namedItem('note') as HTMLTextAreaElement)?.value,\n                      };\n\n                      // Validate using the new helper\n                      const errs = validateProfile(payload);\n                      setProfileErrors(errs);\n\n                      // Mark all required fields as touched to show errors if any\n                      const touchedState: Record<string, boolean> = {};\n                      (settings?.requiredFields || []).forEach((f) => (touchedState[f] = true));\n                      if (errs.city || errs.address) {\n                        touchedState.city = true;\n                        touchedState.address = true;\n                      }\n                      setProfileTouched((prev) => ({ ...prev, ...touchedState }));\n\n                      if (Object.keys(errs).length > 0) {\n                        const firstError = Object.values(errs)[0];\n                        toast.error(firstError || 'Vui lòng kiểm tra lại thông tin!');\n                        return;\n                      }\n\n                      try {\n                        const submitBtn = form.querySelector('button[type=\"submit\"]') as HTMLButtonElement;\n                        if (submitBtn) submitBtn.disabled = true;\n                        const res = await updateStudent(student.id, payload);\n                        if (res.success) {\n                          toast.success('Đã ghi nhận thay đổi hồ sơ.');\n                          onRefresh?.();\n                          onClose();\n                        } else {\n                          toast.error(res.message || res.error || 'Có lỗi xảy ra khi lưu học viên.');\n                        }\n                      } catch (err: any) {\n                        toast.error(err?.message || 'Lỗi khi lưu thông tin. Vui lòng thử lại sau.');\n                      } finally {\n                        const submitBtn = form.querySelector('button[type=\"submit\"]') as HTMLButtonElement;\n                        if (submitBtn) submitBtn.disabled = false;\n                      }\n                    }}\n                    className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-6 gap-y-5 animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-2 duration-300\"\n                  >\n                    <FieldWrapper\n                      label=\"Họ và tên\"\n                      required={isFieldRequired('name')}\n                      error={profileErrors.name}\n                      touched={profileTouched.name}\n                    >\n                      <input\n                        name=\"name\"\n                        required={isFieldRequired('name')}\n                        type=\"text\"\n                        defaultValue={\n                          fullData?.user_id?.last_name\n                            ? `${fullData.user_id.last_name} ${fullData.user_id.first_name}`\n                            : student.name\n                        }\n                        onBlur={() => setProfileTouched((prev) => ({ ...prev, name: true }))}\n                        onChange={(e) => {\n                          const val = e.target.value;\n                          if (profileTouched.name) {\n                            setProfileErrors((prev) => ({\n                              ...prev,\n                              name: val.trim() ? '' : 'Vui lòng nhập Họ và tên.',\n\n[1596 more lines in file. Use offset=880 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776960900161}}
{"type":"message","id":"937c8312","parentId":"07ebed5d","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:15:08.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The `validateProfile` function validates all fields in `settings?.requiredFields || []`. If the system settings has `tuition` or `fee` in the `requiredFields`, it would validate it.\n\nBut looking at the code:\n1. `validateProfile` only validates fields that are in `settings?.requiredFields`\n2. The error \"vui lòng nhập tuition\" would come from `requiredConfig.forEach` if `tuition` is in the `requiredFields` array from settings\n\nThe problem is that `tuition` / `fee` might be in the `requiredFields` in the settings database, and the user doesn't want it to be required.\n\n\nThe real issue is that `currentFee` is tied to the tuition input field, and while there's logic to auto-populate it from the selected course, if the user leaves it blank or clears it, the validation fails because `fee` is marked as required in the settings. The cleanest solution would be to exclude `fee` from the required fields in the settings entirely, or handle the auto-population logic differently so it doesn't conflict with the validation. I'm going to remove `fee`/`tuition` from the required validation list entirely, but I need to account for the fact that `payloadKey` mapping handles `address` → `address` and `cccd` → `identity_number`, so `fee` would map to `fee` directly in the validation check.","thinkingSignature":"495b6accf059f378249e57549f5e6a458c052e2c29912e4bb0d3ebb551d224fb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8sxn0ci4hn2j_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/components/students/StudentDetailDrawer.tsx","offset":1115,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":900,"output":377,"cacheRead":35013,"cacheWrite":930,"totalTokens":37220,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776960900170,"responseId":"06397885bb63d918b7ef1ec4821e9ade"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e2a8c5e","parentId":"937c8312","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:15:08.779Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8sxn0ci4hn2j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                        value={selectedCourse}\n                        onChange={(val) => {\n                          setSelectedCourse(val);\n                          if (profileTouched.course) {\n                            setProfileErrors((prev) => ({\n                              ...prev,\n                              course: val ? '' : 'Vui lòng chọn Khóa học.',\n                            }));\n                          }\n                        }}\n                        onCourseSelect={(course) => {\n                          if (!isFeeManuallySet) {\n                            // Priority: Course Fee > Rank Fee\n                            if (course && course.course_fee) {\n                              setCurrentFee(formatNumberWithDots(course.course_fee.toString()));\n                            } else if (selectedRank) {\n                              const selectedCat = licenseCats.find((lc: any) => lc._id === selectedRank);\n                              if (selectedCat && selectedCat.fee) {\n                                setCurrentFee(formatNumberWithDots(selectedCat.fee.replace(/[^0-9]/g, '')));\n                              }\n                            }\n                          }\n                        }}\n                        initialCourseName={fullData?.enrollment?.course_name || ''}\n                        className={`w-full text-sm font-medium transition-all ${\n                          profileTouched.course && profileErrors.course ? 'text-rose-600' : 'text-gray-700'\n                        }`}\n                      />\n                    </FieldWrapper>\n\n                    <FieldWrapper label=\"Tổng học phí (VNĐ)\" colSpan={1}>\n                      <div className=\"relative\">\n                        <input\n                          type=\"text\"\n                          name=\"fee\"\n                          value={currentFee}\n                          onChange={(e) => {\n                            const val = formatNumberWithDots(e.target.value);\n                            setCurrentFee(val);\n                            setIsFeeManuallySet(val.trim() !== '' && val.trim() !== '0');\n                          }}\n                          onFocus={(e) => {\n                            if (e.target.value === '0') setCurrentFee('');\n                          }}\n                          className=\"w-full px-3 py-2.5 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 focus:border-indigo-500 text-sm font-bold text-indigo-600\"\n                          placeholder=\"0\"\n                        />\n                        <span className=\"absolute right-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-[10px] font-black text-gray-400\">\n                          VNĐ\n                        </span>\n\n[1311 more lines in file. Use offset=1165 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776960908772}}
{"type":"message","id":"651fdec9","parentId":"2e2a8c5e","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:15:17.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The `Tổng học phí` field maps to `fee` in the payload, and it's validated by `validateProfile`. If `fee` is in `settings.requiredFields`, it would require it.\n\nThe fix should be:\n1. Always treat `fee` as optional in `validateProfile` (never require it)\n2. If the user hasn't manually set the fee and has selected a course, auto-populate from course\n3. The auto-population already works via `onCourseSelect`\n\nActually, looking at the code flow:\n- When a course is selected via `onCourseSelect`, `setCurrentFee` is called with the course fee (if not manually set)\n\n\n- But `setSelectedCourse(val)` is called first, then `onCourseSelect(course)` is called\n- The `onCourseSelect` callback is defined in the `CourseSelectDropdown` component and fires when a course is selected from the dropdown\n\nThe issue is that the `Tổng học phí` field might be required by settings, so I need to make `fee` always optional in the validation logic, regardless of what the settings say.\n\nUpdating validation...","thinkingSignature":"cdb37cb193c70a6235313da2854f7f2e4f323ef7688bcd9b5197a13f16952700"},{"type":"text","text":"\nMình đã hiểu rõ vấn đề. Mình sẽ:\n1. Loại `fee` khỏi validation bắt buộc trong `validateProfile` (luôn là optional)\n2. Auto-fill từ khóa học đã chọn (logic hiện có đã gần đúng rồi)\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_74xsd59wu8aw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git checkout -b fix/tuition-fee-optional-20260423","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_74xsd59wu8aw_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/components/students/StudentDetailDrawer.tsx","offset":405,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ah