{"type":"message","id":"c5b7e686","parentId":"95718194","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:22:58.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The AddStudentModal.tsx validation at line 183 no longer has the `tuition` check - my fix worked there.\n\nBut wait - the user is still seeing \"Vui lòng nhập tuition\". Maybe this is from the backend validation! Let me look at the backend more carefully. Let me check if the backend has a requiredFields validation that includes `tuition` and what error it produces.\n\nActually wait - looking at the backend code:\n```typescript\nconst MAPPING: Record<string, { field: string; label: string }> = {\n  ...\n  // No tuition or fee\n};\n\nfor (const fieldId of settings.requiredFields) {\n  const mapping = MAPPING[fieldId];\n  if (!mapping) continue; // Skips unknown fields\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSo if the backend settings have `tuition` in requiredFields, it would be skipped because there's no mapping for it. But the user says the error is showing... \n\nLet me trace through AddStudentModal's handleSubmit to see how it processes the form data and when that error message would actually get triggered.\n\nLooking at the flow: the modal validates the form first, then calls createStudent with the payload. The error message \"Vui lòng nhập tuition\" is coming from the client-side validation in AddStudentModal.tsx, which I need to track down and fix. I'm also noticing there's a similar validation function in ImportTuitionModal that might be handling the same thing differently.\n\nThe user mentioned they're seeing the error in the profile page, but AddStudentModal is the registration modal. Let me reconsider whether this could be triggered from a different component or if there's another validation path I'm missing—maybe through the backend response or a toast notification from the API. The exact string \"Vui lòng nhập tuition\" doesn't match anything in the backend code, so it's definitely frontend-generated. Looking at 