{"type":"message","id":"1beaa573","parentId":"ee2d9665","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:14.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the `findAll` aggregate function at line 349 to understand the full query. The issue might be in the aggregate pipeline.","thinkingSignature":"3a88f58b9d8bc4e0ea3b6cfc7cf75524378e85afb6150db3abbbe39deff4c094"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3o82ox4iyrn0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts","offset":326,"limit":100}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":725,"output":100,"cacheRead":67290,"cacheWrite":961,"totalTokens":69076,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962349802,"responseId":"06397e2fef397f13fc8f37ab9ce922fa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8029952c","parentId":"1beaa573","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:14.093Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3o82ox4iyrn0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  async findAll(\n    filters: any = {},\n    options: PaginationOptions = { page: 1, limit: 10 },\n    currentUser?: any,\n  ): Promise<PaginatedResult<IStudent>> {\n    const { page = 1, limit = 25 } = options;\n    const skip = (page - 1) * limit;\n\n    const mongoFilters = await this._buildFilters(filters, currentUser);\n    const statusFilter = mongoFilters.status_detail;\n    const debtFilter = mongoFilters.debt_status;\n\n    // Remove complex filters from root to calculate statistics correctly\n    const baseFilters = { ...mongoFilters };\n    delete baseFilters.status_detail;\n    delete baseFilters.debt_status;\n\n    logger.info(`[Repository] Base Query Filters: ${JSON.stringify(baseFilters)}`);\n    logger.info(`[Repository] Status Filter: ${statusFilter}, Debt Filter: ${debtFilter}`);\n\n    const isSimple = filters.simple === 'true' || filters.simple === true;\n\n    try {\n      const results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n        { $match: baseFilters }, // Root match uses relaxed filters\n\n        // Hoist multi-enrollment data for root filtering and listing\n        {\n          $lookup: {\n            from: 'coursestudents',\n            let: { studentId: '$_id' },\n            pipeline: [{ $match: { $expr: { $eq: ['$student_id', '$$studentId'] } } }, { $sort: { created_at: 1 } }],\n            as: 'enrollments',\n          },\n        },\n        { $addFields: { latest_enrollment: { $arrayElemAt: ['$enrollments', -1] } } }, // Fetch latest\n        {\n          $addFields: {\n            status_detail: {\n              $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.status_detail', { $ifNull: ['$status_detail', 'Chờ KSK'] }],\n            },\n            progress_flags: {\n              $ifNull: [\n                '$latest_enrollment.progress_flags',\n                {\n                  theory_completed: false,\n                  sand_yard_completed: false,\n                  simulation_completed: false,\n                  dat_completed: false,\n                  cabin_completed: false,\n                  graduation_eligible: false,\n                },\n              ],\n            },\n            health_check: '$latest_enrollment.health_check',\n            latest_course_id: '$latest_enrollment.course_id',\n            current_license_category_id: {\n              $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.license_category_id', '$license_category_id'],\n            },\n            effective_license_category_id: {\n              $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.license_category_id', '$license_category_id'],\n            },\n            tuition_paid: { $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.paid_fee', 0] },\n            tuition_total: { $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.fee', 0] },\n            tuition_balance: { $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment.balance', 0] },\n            has_course: {\n              $cond: [{ $ifNull: ['$latest_enrollment', false] }, true, false],\n            },\n          },\n        },\n        {\n          $addFields: {\n            tuition_remaining: { $max: [0, { $subtract: ['$tuition_total', '$tuition_paid'] }] },\n          },\n        },\n\n        {\n          $facet: {\n            data: [\n              ...(filters.theory === 'true' || filters.theory === true\n                ? [{ $match: { 'progress_flags.theory_completed': true } }]\n                : []),\n              ...(filters.cabin === 'true' || filters.cabin === true\n                ? [{ $match: { 'progress_flags.cabin_completed': true } }]\n                : []),\n              ...(filters.sand === 'true' || filters.sand === true\n                ? [{ $match: { 'progress_flags.sand_yard_completed': true } }]\n                : []),\n              ...(filters.eligible_for_graduation === 'true' || filters.eligible_for_graduation === true\n                ? [{ $match: { 'progress_flags.graduation_eligible': true } }]\n                : []),\n              ...(statusFilter === 'Đã vào khóa' ? [{ $match: { status_detail: 'Đã vào khóa' } }] : []),\n              ...(statusFilter === 'Chưa vào khóa' ? [{ $match: { status_detail: 'Chưa vào khóa' } }] : []),\n              ...(statusFilter === 'Chờ xếp khóa' ? [{ $match: { status_detail: 'Chờ xếp khóa' } }] : []),\n              ...(statusFilter === 'Học viên tồn' ? [{ $match: { status_detail: 'Học viên tồn' } }] : []),\n              ...(statusFilter &&\n              !['Đã vào khóa', 'Chưa vào khóa', 'Chờ xếp khóa', 'Học viên tồn'].includes(statusFilter)\n                ? [{ $match: { status_detail: statusFilter } }]\n                : []),\n              ...(debtFilter === 'debt'\n\n[521 more lines in file. Use offset=426 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962354086}}
{"type":"message","id":"96e336c7","parentId":"8029952c","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:25.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the query, but I don't see any filtering for `role` in the student list query. The issue might be that the backend's student list returns all users who are in the `students` collection, and the teacher information might be coming from the `user_id` lookup (where teacher data might be mixing in).\n\nWait, let me reconsider. Looking at the code, the issue is likely not in the student repository, but rather:\n1. The `users` lookup in the student aggregate returns all user fields including teacher info\n2. OR the student list is including users with `role === 'teacher'`\n\nLet me check if there's any user role filtering in the student model query. \n\nI should also look at the frontend display logic to see if it's correctly filtering which fields to show from the user object. Let me ask the user for clarification about what they mean by \"showing teacher information\" — whether teachers are appearing as rows in the list or if teacher details are embedded within student rows.\n\nLooking at the aggregate pipeline, it matches against `StudentModel` and joins with `users`, so it should only return students. But I'm noticing the mapped students object includes fields like `phone`, `email`, `rank`, `region`, and `status`, which suggests these could be pulling in data from the user lookup.\n\nThe issue might be that teacher accounts are being created in the student system itself, or there's a user role distinction I'm missing. Let me check the backend to see if there's role-based filtering that would exclude teachers from appearing in the student list.","thinkingSignature":"72fe579e63774546788b91edb88d63e91d51ebe607f1fe6ef0883144e5d91949"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5tao25r7jw6d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"is_deleted\\|role\\|user.*role\\|StudentModel\\|findAll\" src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5tao25r7jw6d_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"role\\|teacher\\|student\\|schema\" src/infrastructure/database/models/student.model.ts | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1215,"output":512,"cacheRead":68120,"cacheWrite":897,"totalTokens":70744,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962354099,"responseId":"06397e33386b0321441e4bb7b9e68535"}}
