{"type":"message","id":"ad386125","parentId":"20b4ef3c","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:34.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that the `StudentModel` uses `collection: 'studentinfos'`. The student model has a `teacher_id` field which is a reference to the `Users` collection. \n\nThe issue might be that:\n1. Teachers are stored in the same `studentinfos` collection (as students) with their own records\n2. OR there's no role-based filtering in the aggregate query\n\nLet me look at the aggregate query to see if it filters by `is_deleted` or any role-related field. Looking at line 349:\n```js\nconst results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n  { $match: baseFilters }, // Root match uses relaxed filters\n\n\n```\n\nThe baseFilters is built from `_buildFilters`. Let me check what filters are applied there.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - the user says \"the student list shows teacher information\". This could mean that when listing students, the `teacher_id` field from the student record is being displayed (as a reference to a teacher user). Or it could mean that teacher user accounts are appearing in the student list.\n\nLet me look at what the `_buildFilters` method does and what `is_deleted` checks are in place.","thinkingSignature":"006593a9080a447ec81905b5f985299ca7032493c6a09f779da7dd6fdc85bb21"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tw0ucrs5m8g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"_buildFilters\\|is_deleted\\|match\\|baseFilters\" src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":561,"output":345,"cacheRead":68912,"cacheWrite":1773,"totalTokens":71591,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962365995,"responseId":"06397e3f