{"type":"message","id":"5232823f","parentId":"a6c7921f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:52.482Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the `addOwnershipFilter` function.","thinkingSignature":"d1b67c6c647760094ee27fe1d4fe57d328202941784dd501a9b3be25d9325568"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nudwekoi3fbm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/utils/queryFilters.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":92,"output":59,"cacheRead":72139,"cacheWrite":620,"totalTokens":72910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962388591,"responseId":"06397e557824dfa78630e1261ccdb717"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d268ab7","parentId":"5232823f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:39:52.498Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nudwekoi3fbm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Role } from '@/domain/constants/rbac';\nimport mongoose from 'mongoose';\n\n/**\n * Automatically injects teacher_id filter if the user is a teacher.\n * Also ensures teacher_id is a proper ObjectId for aggregation pipelines.\n */\nexport function addOwnershipFilter(user: any, query: any = {}) {\n  if (!user) return query;\n\n  if (user.role === Role.TEACHER) {\n    const teacherId = user.id || user._id || user.teacher_id;\n    if (!teacherId) return query;\n\n    // We use snake_case teacher_id as per project standard in models\n    return {\n      ...query,\n      teacher_id: typeof teacherId === 'string' ? new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(teacherId) : teacherId,\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Superadmin doesn't filter by owner\n  return query;\n}\n\n/**\n * Checks if a user has access to a specific resource instance.\n */\nexport function canAccessResource(user: any, resource: any): boolean {\n  if (!resource) return false;\n  if (!user) return false;\n\n  // Superadmin bypass\n  if (user.role === Role.SUPERADMIN) return true;\n\n  if (user.role === Role.TEACHER) {\n    const userId = (user.id || user._id || user.teacher_id)?.toString();\n    const resourceOwnerId = (resource.teacher_id || resource.teacherId)?.toString();\n\n    return userId === resourceOwnerId;\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962392492}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb512a79","parentId":"0d268ab7","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:02.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue more clearly. The `addOwnershipFilter` function doesn't add `is_deleted: false` filter. Let me check if the `_buildFilters` adds `is_deleted: false`.\n\nLooking at line 334-350 in the student repository:\n```js\nconst mongoFilters = await this._buildFilters(filters, currentUser);\nconst statusFilter = mongoFilters.status_detail;\nconst debtFilter = mongoFilters.debt_status;\n\nconst baseFilters = { ...mongoFilters };\ndelete baseFilters.status_detail;\ndelete baseFilters.debt_status;\n\nconst results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n  { $match: baseFilters }, // Root match uses relaxed filters\n```\n\nThe `baseFilters` comes from `_buildFilters`. Let me look at what `_buildFilters` returns and whether it includes `is_deleted: false`. Looking at the grep, I don't see `is_deleted: false` being added in `_buildFilters`. But looking at the main query at line 349 - the aggregate starts with `{ $match: baseFilters }`. If `is_deleted: false` is not in `baseFilters`, then soft-deleted records would be included.\n\nBut the user says \"showing teacher information\". I think the most likely issue is that the `StudentModel` is used to store student info, and the user model stores both students and teachers. When looking up `user_id` in the aggregate, the user's role isn't being checked, so a user who is also a teacher might appear as a student.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The `studentinfos` collection stores student records. Teachers might be stored in the `users` collection with `role: 'teacher'`. The `user_id` in `studentinfos` points to a user. But I don't think teachers are stored in `studentinfos`.\n\nWait, I should re-examine the `_buildFilters` function to see if it includes the `is_deleted: false` filter, since that's the most obvious culprit for showing unwanted records.","thinkingSignature":"d18039c0e43b598ff0cd3fd3372c508a9fadb7ee807fd69341e3e8cceccd8062"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2590ux0wmf67_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts","offset":526,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":384,"output":482,"cacheRead":72617,"cacheWrite":234,"totalTokens":73717,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962392505,"responseId":"06397e594bf8eda83836b6e73f405081"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d3d7eb3","parentId":"fb512a79","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:02.792Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2590ux0wmf67_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  private async _buildFilters(filters: any, currentUser?: any): Promise<any> {\n    const {\n      search,\n      status,\n      license_category_id,\n      region_id,\n      vehicle_type,\n      course_id,\n      unassigned,\n      debt_status,\n      teacher_id,\n    } = filters;\n    let mongoFilters: any = {};\n    const conditions: any[] = [];\n\n    // Apply RBAC Ownership Filter\n    if (currentUser?.role === Role.TEACHER) {\n      const assignedIds = await this.getAssignedStudentIds(currentUser.id || currentUser._id);\n      mongoFilters._id = { $in: assignedIds };\n      logger.info(`[StudentRepository] Teacher ${currentUser.id} assigned student count: ${assignedIds.length}`);\n    } else if (currentUser) {\n      mongoFilters = addOwnershipFilter(currentUser, mongoFilters);\n    }\n\n    if (search && typeof search === 'string') {\n      const trimmedSearch = search.trim();\n      if (trimmedSearch) {\n        const matchingUsers = await UserModel.find(\n          {\n            $or: [\n              {\n                $expr: {\n                  $regexMatch: {\n                    input: { $concat: ['$first_name', ' ', '$last_name'] },\n                    regex: trimmedSearch,\n                    options: 'i',\n                  },\n                },\n              },\n              {\n\n[381 more lines in file. Use offset=566 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962402776}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5abd78b","parentId":"2d3d7eb3","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:12.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `_buildFilters` doesn't add `is_deleted: false` to the mongoFilters. However, looking at the main `findAll` at line 326, the aggregate pipeline starts with `{ $match: baseFilters }` which doesn't include `is_deleted`. But the `findById` at line 66 does include `addOwnershipFilter`.\n\nWait, let me look more carefully at the student aggregate query. The aggregate starts at line 349:\n```js\nconst results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n  { $match: baseFilters },\n  ...\n])\n```\n\nAnd `baseFilters` doesn't include `is_deleted: false`. \n\nThe search logic at line 555 does add `is_deleted: false` when finding matching users, but then at line 595 it only passes `_id: { $in: matchingIds }` to the pipeline without the deletion flag, which means soft-deleted records could still be included in the final results.\n\nActually, wait—looking at the aggregate pipeline more carefully, it starts with `{ $match: baseFilters }`, so if `baseFilters` contains `is_deleted: false`, that would filter out deleted records at the very beginning. The search results just narrow down which records to include based on the search term, but the deletion filter should already be applied upstream.\n\nLet me trace through `_buildFilters` more carefully to see whether it's actually setting that `is_deleted: false` condition.","thinkingSignature":"f400ba3667fa1f6fcffa3e919d8ca6d804e74aaeb51aeee9baf61f8536391ecc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n1kpr7gsvgcm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts","offset":590,"limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":369,"output":363,"cacheRead":72787,"cacheWrite":871,"totalTokens":74390,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962402807,"responseId":"06397e646505cb7523eb589deff2e789"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6f44bfc","parentId":"b5abd78b","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:12.142Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n1kpr7gsvgcm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    if (license_category_id && license_category_id !== 'Tất cả' && license_category_id !== 'Mọi hạng') {\n      let catId: any;\n      if (mongoose.Types.ObjectId.isValid(license_category_id)) {\n        catId = new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(license_category_id);\n      } else {\n        const cat = await LicenseCategoryModel.findOne({\n          $or: [{ code: license_category_id }, { name: license_category_id }],\n        })\n          .select('_id')\n          .lean()\n          .exec();\n        catId = cat ? (cat as any)._id : null;\n      }\n\n      if (catId) {\n        const studentIdsWithCategory = await CourseStudentModel.find({ license_category_id: catId })\n          .distinct('student_id')\n          .exec();\n        conditions.push({ _id: { $in: studentIdsWithCategory } });\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (region_id && !['Tất cả', 'Tất cả khu vực'].includes(region_id)) {\n      if (mongoose.Types.ObjectId.isValid(region_id)) {\n        mongoFilters.region_id = region_id;\n      } else {\n        const city = await CityModel.findOne({ name: region_id }).select('_id').lean().exec();\n        mongoFilters.region_id = city ? (city as any)._id : new mongoose.Types.ObjectId();\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (course_id && course_id !== 'Tất cả') {\n      const studentIdsInCourse = await CourseStudentModel.find({ course_id }).distinct('student_id').exec();\n      conditions.push({ _id: { $in: studentIdsInCourse } });\n    }\n\n    if (unassigned) {\n      const enrolledStudentIds = await CourseStudentModel.find().distinct('student_id').exec();\n      conditions.push({ _id: { $nin: enrolledStudentIds } });\n    }\n\n    if (vehicle_type && vehicle_type !== 'Tất cả') {\n      const matchingCats = await LicenseCategoryModel.find({ type: vehicle_type }).distinct('_id').exec();\n      const studentIdsWithVehicle = await CourseStudentModel.find({ license_category_id: { $in: matchingCats } })\n        .distinct('student_id')\n        .exec();\n      conditions.push({ _id: { $in: studentIdsWithVehicle } });\n    }\n\n    if (debt_status && debt_status !== 'Tất cả') {\n      mongoFilters.debt_status = debt_status;\n    }\n\n    if (teacher_id) {\n      const teacherObjectId = new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(teacher_id);\n      const studentIdsWithTeacher = await CourseStudentModel.find({ teacher_id: teacherObjectId })\n        .distinct('student_id')\n        .exec();\n      conditions.push({\n        $or: [{ _id: { $in: studentIdsWithTeacher.map((id) => id as any) } }, { teacher_id: teacherObjectId }],\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (conditions.length > 0) {\n      mongoFilters.$and = conditions;\n    }\n\n    return mongoFilters;\n  }\n\n  private _getSummaryPipeline(): any[] {\n    return [\n      { $lookup: { from: 'users', localField: 'user_id', foreignField: '_id', as: 'user' } },\n      { $unwind: '$user' },\n      {\n        $lookup: {\n          from: 'licensecategories',\n          localField: 'effective_license_category_id',\n          foreignField: '_id',\n          as: 'license_info',\n\n[277 more lines in file. Use offset=670 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962412131}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c7b3b23","parentId":"a6f44bfc","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:25.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that `_buildFilters` doesn't add `is_deleted: false` by default. The only place it might be added is in the search condition when searching by user name/phone/identity. But if there's no search, `is_deleted: false` is not applied.\n\nHowever, this would cause soft-deleted students to appear, not teachers. The user says \"showing teacher information.\"\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `StudentModel` stores student info. The `teacher_id` field is a reference to the `Users` collection. When a student has a teacher, the teacher's info might be getting mixed in somehow.\n\nActually, I think the most likely scenario is that:1. \n\nThere are user accounts in the system that have `role: 'teacher'` AND are also stored in `studentinfos` as students, or teachers are being added as students through the \"Add Student\" form. I should check the user model and look at the `users` collection to see if teachers appear there and whether they're also in `studentinfos`. I'm also wondering if the aggregate query's `$lookup` from `users` might be pulling in teacher information that gets displayed somehow.\n\nLet me reconsider—maybe teachers were initially created as students and then their role was changed in the Users collection, but they still exist in `studentinfos`. The most direct fix would be adding `is_deleted: false` to the base query and filtering by user role to exclude teachers. But first, I should clarify with the user exactly what \"showing teacher information\" means—probably teacher names or IDs mixed into the student list. Looking at the frontend mapping, I can see how student data gets transformed with fields like ID, student code, name, phone, and email pulled from the user object.\n\nThe issue is becoming clearer: teachers might be stored in the `studentinfos` collection themselves, so they're being queried as students. I need to check if the student query filters by user role or type, since the `_buildFilters` function doesn't seem to be doing that. The cleanest solution would be adding an `is_deleted: false` filter to the base query and ensuring teachers can't be added as students in the first place.\n\nLooking at how users are created in the backend, I need to trace the flow: when a student registers or an admin creates one, a user gets made with a specific role, then a student info record follows. Teachers should have `role: 'teacher'` in the Users collection but shouldn't have corresponding entries in StudentInfos. If teachers are showing up in the student list, it's likely because there's no role filter preventing them from being queried. Let me add `is_deleted: false` to the base query as a starting point and see if that resolves it, though I should verify whether the StudentInfos schema even has a role field to filter on.","thinkingSignature":"5e1ad53711514c94e1c7f2e617435cdf1a993fb902a1e5a091fd94179cc7f594"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g98ysad2pjfr_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/student.model.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":826,"output":631,"cacheRead":73171,"cacheWrite":1160,"totalTokens":75788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962412149,"responseId":"06397e6de6fb9ccd9cc972cdc6530c6a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"58c0c1c3","parentId":"8c7b3b23","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:25.489Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g98ysad2pjfr_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\nimport { IUser } from './user.model';\n\nexport interface IStudent extends Document {\n  user_id: Types.ObjectId | IUser; // Can be ID or populated User object\n  card_id?: string | null;\n  profile_created_at?: Date | null;\n  email_verified_at?: Date | null;\n  lead_manager?: string | null;\n  region_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  license_category_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  course_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  student_code?: string | null;\n  teacher_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  balance?: any;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n  is_deleted: boolean;\n  deleted_at: Date | null;\n  // Merged fields from Enrollment for UI/Tests (Source of truth is CourseStudent)\n  status_detail?: string;\n}\n\nconst StudentSchema = new Schema<IStudent>(\n  {\n    user_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', required: true, index: true },\n    balance: {\n      type: Schema.Types.Decimal128,\n      default: 0,\n      get: (v: any) => (v ? parseFloat(v.toString()) : 0),\n    },\n    card_id: { type: String, default: null },\n    profile_created_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n    email_verified_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n    lead_manager: { type: String, default: null },\n    course_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Courses', default: null },\n    license_category_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'LicenseCategories', default: null },\n    student_code: { type: String, default: null, index: true },\n    teacher_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', default: null, index: true },\n\n    // Extension\n    region_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Cities', default: null },\n    is_deleted: { type: Boolean, default: false, index: true },\n    deleted_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n\n    // Merged fields for UI/Tests (Primary source is CourseStudent)\n    status_detail: { type: String, default: 'Chờ KSK' },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    collection: 'studentinfos',\n  },\n);\n\nStudentSchema.index({ region_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ created_at: -1, is_deleted: 1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ course_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ license_category_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\n\nif (mongoose.models.StudentInfos) {\n  mongoose.deleteModel('StudentInfos');\n}\nexport const StudentModel = mongoose.model<IStudent>('StudentInfos', StudentSchema, 'studentinfos');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962425481}}
{"type":"message","id":"700b5fde","parentId":"58c0c1c3","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:40.379Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `StudentModel` has `is_deleted: false` as a default, but the aggregate query doesn't filter by it. This is a bug - soft-deleted students would appear in the list.\n\nBut the user says \"showing teacher information\" which is different from \"showing deleted students\". \n\nLet me think about this from a different angle. The issue might be:\n1. Teachers are created as users with `role: 'teacher'`\n2. These teacher users have user accounts\n3. There might be student info records created for these teacher accounts (perhaps by mistake or during testing)\n4. When listing students, these teacher-associated student records appear\n\n\n5. When the aggregate does a `$lookup` on the `users` collection, if a teacher has a student record, their teacher role gets pulled in and potentially displayed\n\nSo the fix is adding `is_deleted: false` to the aggregate match and ensuring the base query filters out records linked to teacher users. The cleanest approach would be to modify the aggregate's initial `$match` stage to include `is_deleted: false` and prevent teacher-linked records from being included.\n\nBut actually, I'm realizing the real issue might be simpler - if teachers have student records created for them (maybe during testing), those would show up as students with teacher information attached. The fix is straightforward: add `is_deleted: false` to the aggregate's base match and check if teachers were mistakenly added as students. Let me examine what the aggregate's first `$match` stage looks like and whether `_buildFilters` already applies this filter.\n\nLooking at the code, `_buildFilters` doesn't include `is_deleted: false` in its returned filters, which means soft-deleted records would be included in the aggregate. I need to add this filter to the base match stage to ensure only active records are returned.\n\nFor excluding teachers from the student list, I can use a `$lookup` with `$match` to filter out users with the teacher role. Let me implement both fixes in the backend aggregate pipeline, and I should also check the student creation flow to see if teachers can be mistakenly added as students.\n\nLooking at the `createStudent` function, there's no role validation—it just creates a student record for any user ID without checking if that user has the student role. The simplest fix is adding `is_deleted: false` to the aggregate's initial match stage, and if teachers are appearing as students, I can add a `$lookup` to filter them out based on their role in the users collection.\n\nImplementing the fix in the backend now...","thinkingSignature":"2bdc3574914c78096b5b898f8117055661d8dd90d7eeba5c575289f72835990d"},{"type":"text","text":"Mình thấy vấn đề. `_buildFilters` không thêm `is_deleted: false` vào query, nên soft-deleted records có thể hiện. Và có thể teacher accounts đang có record trong `studentinfos`. Mình fix cả 2 ở backend.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v71kp4qce9so_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git checkout -b fix/exclude-teachers-from-student-list-20260423","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":720,"output":680,"cacheRead":73963,"cacheWrite":1766,"totalTokens":77129,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962425504,"responseId":"06397e7a4be6a8f67a3b9546781db525"}}
