{"type":"message","id":"78248651","parentId":"3b839af6","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:40:51.867Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the aggregate starts with `{ $match: baseFilters }`. I need to add `is_deleted: false` to the `baseFilters` and also add a `$lookup` to filter out users with `role: 'teacher'`.\n\nThe cleanest approach is to:\n1. Add `is_deleted: false` to `baseFilters` \n2. After the `$lookup` to users, add a `$match` to filter out records where the user has `role: 'teacher'`\n\nBut since this is a MongoDB aggregate, I need to be careful about the order. Let me:1. Add `is_deleted: false` to `baseFilters`\n\n\n2. After the `$lookup` to users (which happens at line 354), add a `$match` to exclude records where the user has `role: 'teacher'`\n\nLet me check what the `$lookup` to users looks like in the aggregate.","thinkingSignature":"ff89109c1781cba6a9110ac668ced1bc963431f8106510cadfa9f6f1ef400f15"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxmipg9gr5hl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts","offset":348,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":353,"output":259,"cacheRead":76385,"cacheWrite":817,"totalTokens":77814,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962445132,"responseId":"06397e8e871d600b0ac156a2384bd82a"}}
