{"type":"message","id":"6a29c9c8","parentId":"35a23948","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:41:11.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The fix is:\n\n1. Add `is_deleted: false` to the `baseFilters` \n2. Add a `$lookup` to `users` to get user role, then filter out records where user role is 'teacher'\n\nLet me make these changes. I'll add the `is_deleted: false` filter and add a `$lookup` + `$match` pipeline stage to filter out teacher users.","thinkingSignature":"bd0435d9c5b64305dba7f55352d3856d2062553f6348a0864917086c8fb3cd6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_anls5ngeupeg_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/repositories/student.repository.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"    try {\n      const results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n        { $match: baseFilters }, // Root match uses relaxed filters\n","newText":"    // Always exclude soft-deleted records\n    baseFilters.is_deleted = false;\n\n    try {\n      const results = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n        { $match: baseFilters }, // Root match uses relaxed filters + is_deleted:false + RBAC\n\n        // Lookup user role to filter out teacher accounts stored as students\n        {\n          $lookup: {\n            from: 'users',\n            localField: 'user_id',\n            foreignField: '_id',\n            as: '_user',\n          },\n        },\n        { $unwind: { path: '$_user', preserveNullAndEmptyArrays: false } },\n        // Exclude records whose underlying user is a teacher\n        { $match: { '_user.role': { $ne: 'teacher' } } },\n"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":158,"output":370,"cacheRead":77985,"cacheWrite":720,"totalTokens":79233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962463429,"responseId":"06397ea050707ee85f1deaf5295ab12