{"type":"message","id":"fbcd30df","parentId":"1058695a","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:49:57.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there are `start_date` and `end_date` fields in both CourseStudentModel and CourseModel. \n\nNow I need to understand:\n- In CourseStudentModel: `start_date`, `end_date` - the enrollment's start/end dates\n- In CourseModel: `start_date`, `end_date` - the course template's start/end dates\n\nFor the feature, I need to track per-enrollment start/end dates. Let me check the CourseStudentModel more.","thinkingSignature":"d87b2eac8b93f3a47857414c5d8766d573d824e4a14f0a8b68cd9dcc15c26ba5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m2eljzuwayiy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/course_student.model.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":149,"output":149,"cacheRead":87300,"cacheWrite":639,"totalTokens":88237,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962991823,"responseId":"063980b16e5f5cc30726826135872fb0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"62464149","parentId":"fbcd30df","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:49:57.082Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m2eljzuwayiy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport interface ICourseStudent extends Document {\n  student_id: Types.ObjectId; // References Student(student_infos)\n  course_id: Types.ObjectId; // References Course(course_infos)\n  stadium_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  teacher_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  sale_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  license_category_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  status: 'unfinished' | 'finished' | 'canceled';\n  km: number;\n  hour: string;\n  fee: number;\n  paid_fee: number;\n  balance?: any; // Treasury balance for this enrollment\n  contract_date?: Date | null;\n  status_detail?: string;\n  progress_flags?: {\n    theory_completed: boolean;\n    sand_yard_completed: boolean;\n    simulation_completed: boolean;\n    dat_completed: boolean;\n    cabin_completed: boolean;\n    graduation_eligible: boolean;\n  };\n  health_check?: {\n    status: string;\n    date: Date | null;\n    hospital: string | null;\n    note: string | null;\n  };\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst CourseStudentSchema = new Schema<ICourseStudent>(\n  {\n    student_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'StudentInfos', required: true, index: true },\n    course_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Courses', required: true, index: true },\n    stadium_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Stadiums', default: null },\n    teacher_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', default: null },\n    sale_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', default: null },\n    license_category_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'LicenseCategories', default: null },\n    status: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: ['unfinished', 'finished', 'canceled'],\n      default: 'unfinished',\n    },\n    km: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n    hour: { type: String, default: '00:00' },\n    fee: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n    paid_fee: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n    balance: {\n      type: Schema.Types.Decimal128,\n      default: 0,\n      get: (v: any) => (v ? parseFloat(v.toString()) : 0),\n    },\n    contract_date: { type: Date, default: null },\n    status_detail: { type: String, default: 'Chờ KSK' },\n    progress_flags: {\n      theory_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n      sand_yard_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n      simulation_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n      dat_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n      cabin_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n      graduation_eligible: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    },\n    health_check: {\n      status: { type: String, enum: ['Chờ khám', 'Đủ điều kiện', 'Không đủ điều kiện'], default: 'Chờ khám' },\n      date: { type: Date, default: null },\n      hospital: { type: String, default: null },\n      note: { type: String, default: null },\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    collection: 'coursestudents',\n  },\n);\n\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ student_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ course_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ status_detail: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ sale_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ 'progress_flags.dat_completed': 1, status_detail: 1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ fee: 1, paid_fee: 1 });\n\nexport const CourseStudentModel =\n  mongoose.models.CourseStudents ||\n  mongoose.model<ICourseStudent>('CourseStudents', CourseStudentSchema, 'coursestudents');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776962997075}}
{"type":"message","id":"74ebf607","parentId":"62464149","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:50:07.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `CourseStudentModel` doesn't have `start_date` and `end_date` fields. Those are in the `CourseModel`. So when the user says \"ngày khai giảng\" and \"ngày kết thúc\", they likely mean the `start_date` and `end_date` from the `CourseModel` (the course template).\n\nBut wait, in a course enrollment context, the `course_id` in `CourseStudent` references the `Course` document which has `start_date` and `end_date`. So I need to:\n\n\n1. Look up the `Course` document for each `CourseStudent` to get the actual `start_date` and `end_date`\n2. Check if the teacher's courses have a `start_date` that matches today and a status of \"Sắp khai giảng\" for opening notifications\n3. Similarly check for `end_date` matching today for closing notifications\n\nNow I need to examine the current Dashboard structure to see what components are already in place.","thinkingSignature":"92bdb36b6a6246df49a39f98140e4daa4e979819a13ac149a5f8affa12d768e4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ru0ioz8nyt31_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls src/app/dashboard/Dashboard/ && wc -l src/app/dashboard/Dashboard/Dashboard.tsx","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ru0ioz8nyt31_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"today\\|start_date\\|end_date\\|notification\\|banner\\|popup\\|welcome\\|feature\" src/app/dashboard/Dashboard/Dashboard.tsx -i | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1008,"output":413,"cacheRead":87721,"cacheWrite":457,"totalTokens":89599,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776962