{"type":"message","id":"9c24f810","parentId":"923aabff","timestamp":"2026-04-23T16:50:58.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the model. The `Course` model has `start_date`, `end_date`. The `CourseStudent` (enrollment) has `teacher_id` and `status_detail`. \n\nBut wait - what does \"khóa khai giảng hôm nay\" mean? Is it:\n1. The `Course` document's `start_date === today`?\n2. The `CourseStudent` enrollment's start date (if it has one)?\n\nLooking at the `CourseStudent` model, it doesn't have `start_date` or `end_date` fields. So it must refer to the `Course` document's dates.\n\n\nSo I need to join `CourseStudent` with `Course` and filter for enrollments where the course starts or ends today, and optionally filter by teacher. But the user specifically mentioned teacher login, so the filter should be on `CourseStudent.teacher_id`. The real question is what status the enrollment should have when the course starts - the `CourseStudent.status_detail` field shows \"Chờ KSK\" as the default, but I need to understand what status it should transition to when the course begins.\n\nLooking at the user's example of \"Sắp khai giảng\" → \"Đang học\", it seems like the course status needs a new state for \"about to start\" that transitions to \"in progress\" on the start date. I should check if the `Course.status` field already supports these states like 'draft', 'ongoing', or 'completed'.","thinkingSignature":"2a2e006f6d64706e9d7f6c4b22ab1fc4397737a457b600b0e3db92737ebc5ee0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2v1j0hkwpqjx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"Sắp KG\\|Sắp khai giảng\\|status.*=.*'Sắp\" src/ --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v node_modules | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":265,"output":433,"cacheRead":90947,"cacheWrite":1068,"totalT