{"type":"message","id":"01e78cf1","parentId":"3c612b12","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:30:11.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user can't see the notification banner. I need to demo it. The issue might be that the `getTodayMilestones` API call needs a valid auth token, or the banner component is not showing because the condition checks `user?.role !== 'teacher'`.\n\nLet me think about what could be wrong:\n1. The API requires auth token - the fetch in the component uses `apiClient` which should include the token\n2. The role check in the component - let me re-check the component code\n\nActually, looking at the `CourseMilestoneBanner.tsx` code I wrote, the issue might be:\n1. The role check uses `localStorage.getItem('user')` - this might not match the actual auth context\n\n\n2. Or the API returns data but the condition `milestones.openingCount === 0 && milestones.closingCount === 0` might be filtering it out\n3. Or the role isn't actually 'teacher' for the test account\n\nI should check if the user role is properly set in localStorage and make sure the banner displays unconditionally for demo purposes. Let me create a test version that bypasses the role check and demonstrates the banner directly.\n\nI could also set up a quick test by temporarily creating a demo with mock data, or checking if the backend API is returning the expected results. Let me verify the actual API response first using curl with the auth token from localStorage.","thinkingSignature":"79df42dbeb9d481d3884112eb4bb6a860dec82d56b658d00870ae9e8368b860a"},{"type":"text","text":"Mình demo cho bạn xem. Trước tiên check API có hoạt động không.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_me2j9r1645sa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"apiClient\\|token\\|Authorization\" src/services/api.ts | head -10","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_me2j9r1645sa_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"getTodayMilestones\\|today-milestones\" src/services/courseService.ts","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":178,"output":494,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":113401,"totalTokens":114073,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776965397090,"responseId":"06398a164e186f9140c08f7e7c183167"}}
{"type":"message","id":"de71b6d3","parentId":"01e78cf1","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:30:11.405Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_me2j9r1645sa_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"18:let refreshSubscribers: { resolve: (token: string) => void; reject: (err: any) => void }[] = [];\n20:const subscribeTokenRefresh = (resolve: (token: string) => void, reject: (err: any) => void) => {\n24:const onTokenRefreshed = (token: string | null, err: any = null) => {\n27:    else if (token) sub.resolve(token);\n41:export const apiClient = async <T = any>(endpoint: string, options: ApiOptions = {}): Promise<T> => {\n78:  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('token') : null;\n81:    ...(token ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } : {}),\n111:            const newToken = data.token;\n112:            localStorage.setItem('token', newToken);\n119:            localStorage.removeItem('token');"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":39,"aggregated":"18:let refreshSubscribers: { resolve: (token: string) => void; reject: (err: any) => void }[] = [];\n20:const subscribeTokenRefresh = (resolve: (token: string) => void, reject: (err: any) => void) => {\n24:const onTokenRefreshed = (token: string | null, err: any = null) => {\n27:    else if (token) sub.resolve(token);\n41:export const apiClient = async <T = any>(endpoint: string, options: ApiOptions = {}): Promise<T> => {\n78:  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('token') : null;\n81:    ...(token ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } : {}),\n111:            const newToken = data.token;\n112:            localStorage.setItem('token', newToken);\n119:            localStorage.removeItem('token');","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776965411397}}
