{"type":"message","id":"ad924e93","parentId":"6543e104","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:30:20.252Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API call uses `apiClient` which includes the auth token from localStorage. The issue might be:\n1. The `getTodayMilestones` function is called with `apiClient('/courses/today-milestones')` which should resolve to the full URL\n2. The role check in the component\n\nLet me create a simple test page that bypasses the role check and shows the banner directly, or better yet, let me modify the banner component to show a demo mode when there's no data, or let me create a standalone demo page.\n\nActually, a better approach: let me create a standalone demo page at `/demo-banner` that shows the banner without any API dependencies. \n\nThis would let the user see exactly what the banner looks like. Looking at the banner component more closely, the problem is likely that when `getTodayMilestones()` fails or returns zero counts, the banner just returns null. The real issue might be that the backend is querying by `teacher_id` on the `CourseStudentModel` when the actual course status is stored in the `CourseModel`, so there's a mismatch in how the data's being filtered.\n\nI should create a demo page that displays the banner with mock data so Khuong can see exactly how it looks without needing to set up test data.","thinkingSignature":"131bf071d38d8e99cbedf9c75ef1e16ef9dd4a23d5215d49ca5c79bb73e3f01a"},{"type":"text","text":"Mình tạo một trang demo riêng để bạn xem banner không cần dữ liệu thật.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6z4ved6ggici_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p src/app/demo-banner/","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":296,"output":376,"cacheRead":113385,"cacheWrite":629,"totalTokens":114686,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheR