{"type":"message","id":"c8080db7","parentId":"de38648c","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:41:38.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is getting \"EMFILE: too many open files\" error when trying to run the QLHV backend. This is a system limit issue - the number of open file descriptors has been exhausted. This often happens when:\n\n1. Many ts-node-dev processes are running and watching many files\n2. The system's ulimit for open files is too low\n3. There are leftover processes or temp files\n\nThe solution is to:\n1. Kill any remaining ts-node-dev/tsx processes\n2. Clean up the temp compiled files\n3. Increase the file descriptor limit\n4. Restart with a simpler command\n\nLet me help fix this.","thinkingSignature":"a898a9751175c934f018231bec4fb4a9f4cd9f00b1f62d30ead78413714f32c6"},{"type":"text","text":"Lỗi \"too many open files\" — hệ thống đã đạt giới hạn file descriptors mở cùng lúc. Mình fix ngay.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6w6kza1opso3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -9 -f \"ts-node-dev\\|tsx.*src\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -9 -f \"node.*ahv-qlhv-be\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1\nrm -rf /tmp/.ts-node* 2>/dev/null; echo \"Đã dọn\"","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":512,"output":291,"cacheRead":119637,"cacheWrite":371,"totalTokens":120811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966088670,"responseId":"06398cca42430ff870b802cc6673dd1f"}}
