{"type":"message","id":"67247a92","parentId":"5f9ca7c8","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:41:50.307Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ulimit is already 65536 which is quite high. The problem is that ts-node-dev creates file watchers for every file in the project, and with many ts-node-dev processes running (there were many instances from the earlier restarts), this can exhaust the limit.\n\nThe fix is to run with `--transpile-only` flag (which we already use) and `--respawn` only when needed. But the main fix is to kill ALL existing ts-node processes first.\n\nLet me try killing by specific PID patterns.","thinkingSignature":"23f952f1fde70cbdfe83a16e00edfcd3eceaf35cd6412df33c4361280e27c274"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_77ui5e0hcujs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill -9 $(ps aux | grep \"ahv-qlhv-be\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}') 2>/dev/null; sleep 1; ps aux | grep \"ahv-qlhv-be\" | grep -v grep | wc -l","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":81,"output":212,"cacheRead":120456,"cacheWrite":422,"totalTokens":121171,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966103317,"responseId":"06398cd88ae9183d8f1cf974d0a41067"}}
