{"type":"message","id":"4e191dd5","parentId":"f6ea2018","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:42:00.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, all ahv-qlhv-be processes are killed. Now let me start the BE with a single instance using ts-node-dev with --transpile-only and --respawn disabled. Also, I should use `--exit-child` flag to prevent child processes from accumulating.Actually, the best approach is to use `npx ts-node-dev` with `--exit-child` flag, or better yet, just use `npx ts-node` for a one-shot startup (not dev mode with file watching). But for development, we want hot reload.\n\nThe issue might be the accumulated number of ts-node-dev instances from all my previous restarts. Now that they're all killed, let me try starting fresh.\n\n\nI'm realizing the real culprit is likely the number of instances running simultaneously rather than a system limit issue. Since we've cleared them all out, starting fresh with ts-node-dev should work fine now.","thinkingSignature":"7b5f61e5385fb4f37333fd4db2393abd820062371a923de5b81700ae01a23fbe"},{"type":"text","text":"Đã kill hết. Giờ start lại BE:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_53wf650lj3z1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"nohup npx ts-node-dev --transpile-only -r tsconfig-paths/register --exit-child src/index.ts > /tmp/ahv-be.log 2>&1 &\necho \"BE started PID: $!\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":5000,"background":true,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":324,"cacheRead":120770,"cacheWrite":342,"totalTokens":121512,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966111448,"responseId":"06398ce1cb1869085a8a2fd9bf9a79e7"}}
