{"type":"message","id":"a2c3c719","parentId":"b31f8393","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:45:37.906Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"6130\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"sender\": \"Khuong\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-23 17:45 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Khuong (6053576134)\",\n  \"id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"Khuong\",\n  \"username\": \"khuowgn\"\n}\n```\n\ntôi muốn được xem banner đó hiện trực tiếp ở dashboard để xem đã đúng ý tôi chưa cơ bạn có thể giúp tôi không"}],"timestamp":1776966337870}}
{"type":"message","id":"30310435","parentId":"a2c3c719","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:45:48.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to see the banner on the actual dashboard without needing teacher data. I should modify the component to always show the banner for demo purposes, or create a way to toggle it. Let me modify the `CourseMilestoneBanner` to always show (for demo) or add a way to trigger it.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to make the banner always show regardless of the API response, using the same demo data. But that would be confusing for production.\n\nA better approach: Let me add a query param or localStorage flag that forces the banner to show for demo purposes. Or even simpler: I'll modify the banner to show itself when there's no milestones data AND we're on the dashboard (for testing purposes).\n\n\nI think the cleanest solution is to add a debug query parameter that forces the banner to display with demo data, so the user can see it in the actual dashboard context without affecting production behavior.","thinkingSignature":"865d35a6b349e4e0f4b750cf77b82324e5d2e0dda68d440ec36c6e1b44afeea3"},{"type":"text","text":"Được, mình chỉnh lại banner để hiện trực tiếp trên dashboard (không cần API) để bạn xem đã đúng ý chưa.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7qog2nuetnbl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"useEffect\\|getTodayMilestones\\|role.*teacher\" src/components/dashboard/CourseMilestoneBanner.tsx | head -15","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":339,"cacheRead":122938,"cacheWrite":238,"totalTokens":123515,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966337907,"responseId":"06398dc31097fd7c131f24e6873e1866"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0600a7b3","parentId":"30310435","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:45:48.772Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7qog2nuetnbl_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3:import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\n6:import { getTodayMilestones, bulkUpdateCourseStatus } from '@/src/services/courseService';\n36:  useEffect(() => {\n42:      if (user?.role !== 'teacher') return;\n47:    getTodayMilestones()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":29,"aggregated":"3:import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\n6:import { getTodayMilestones, bulkUpdateCourseStatus } from '@/src/services/courseService';\n36:  useEffect(() => {\n42:      if (user?.role !== 'teacher') return;\n47:    getTodayMilestones()","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776966348765}}
{"type":"message","id":"66c3f272","parentId":"0600a7b3","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:46:03.694Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll modify the CourseMilestoneBanner to:\n1. Try the API first\n2. If API returns no milestones or error, show demo data if on the dashboard\n3. Or better: add a query param `?debug=banner` to force show with demo data\n\nActually the simplest approach: always show demo data if no API data. But this could confuse real users.\n\nBetter approach: Add a `DEMO_MODE=true` prop or check for a localStorage key `debugBanner`.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: The banner should show real data when available. If no data (no milestones today), it won't show. \n\nTo make it demo-friendly, I'll check if the user has `role=teacher` and either show real data from the API or fallback to demo data for visibility. Let me refactor the component to handle both scenarios.","thinkingSignature":"7b44c93e71edbd67e5754eeef7ad480471bbdf6734ecb92c64021999151ba9be"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5npz1rhk2bw0_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/components/dashboard/CourseMilestoneBanner.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"interface Milestones {\n  openingCourses: CourseMilestone[];\n  closingCourses: CourseMilestone[];\n  openingCount: number;\n  closingCount: number;\n}\n\ninterface CourseMilestoneBannerProps {\n  teacherId?: string;\n}\n\nconst CourseMilestoneBanner: React.FC<CourseMilestoneBannerProps> = () => {\n  const [milestones, setMilestones] = useState<Milestones | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [processing, setProcessing] = useState(false);\n  const [showReviewModal, setShowReviewModal] = useState(false);\n  const [reviewTab, setReviewTab] = useState<'opening' | 'closing'>('opening');\n  const [selectedCourses, setSelectedCourses] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());\n  const [dismissed, setDismissed] = useState(false);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Only show for teacher role\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem('user');\n    if (!stored) return;\n    try {\n      const user = JSON.parse(stored);\n      if (user?.role !== 'teacher') return;\n    } catch {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    getTodayMilestones()\n      .then((res: any) => {\n        if (res?.success && (res.data?.openingCount > 0 || res.data?.closingCount > 0)) {\n          setMilestones(res.data);\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(() => {})\n      .finally(() => setLoading(false));\n  }, []);\n","newText":"// Demo data for testing when no real data available\nconst DEMO_MILESTONES: Milestones = {\n  openingCourses: [\n    { _id: 'demo1', name: 'Khóa B2 - Sáng thứ 2', start_date: new Date().toISOString(), student_count: 28 },\n    { _id: 'demo2', name: 'Khóa B1 - Tối thứ 2', start_date: new Date().toISOString(), student_count: 35 },\n  ],\n  closingCourses: [\n    { _id: 'demo3', name: 'Khóa A1 - Sáng thứ 7', end_date: new Date().toISOString(), student_count: 22 },\n  ],\n  openingCount: 2,\n  closingCount: 1,\n};\n\ninterface Milestones {\n  openingCourses: CourseMilestone[];\n  closingCourses: CourseMilestone[];\n  openingCount: number;\n  closingCount: number;\n}\n\ninterface CourseMilestoneBannerProps {\n  teacherId?: string;\n  /** Force show demo banner (for preview/testing) */\n  demoMode?: boolean;\n}\n\nconst CourseMilestoneBanner: React.FC<CourseMilestoneBannerProps> = ({ demoMode = false }) => {\n  const [milestones, setMilestones] = useState<Milestones | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [processing, setProcessing] = useState(false);\n  const [showReviewModal, setShowReviewModal] = useState(false);\n  const [reviewTab, setReviewTab] = useState<'opening' | 'closing'>('opening');\n  const [selectedCourses, setSelectedCourses] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());\n  const [dismissed, setDismissed] = useState(false);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Demo mode: show demo data immediately\n    if (demoMode) {\n      setMilestones(DEMO_MILESTONES);\n      setLoading(false);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Only show for teacher role\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem('user');\n    if (!stored) { setLoading(false); return; }\n    try {\n      const user = JSON.parse(stored);\n      if (user?.role !== 'teacher') { setLoading(false); return; }\n    } catch { setLoading(false); return; }\n\n    getTodayMilestones()\n      .then((res: any) => {\n        if (res?.success && (res.data?.openingCount > 0 || res.data?.closingCount > 0)) {\n          setMilestones(res.data);\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(() => {})\n      .finally(() => setLoading(false));\n  }, [demoMode]);\n"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":116,"output":1277,"cacheRead":123482,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124875,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966348790,"responseId":"06398dce6e5887b49025d122d398afd0"}}
