{"type":"message","id":"e5af22be","parentId":"8f4cbaff","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:47:37.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking:\n1. Turn off demo mode (remove the demo banner)\n2. But they want to know if the logic to detect which courses start/end today is actually implemented\n\nThe answer is: **yes, the logic IS already implemented in the backend.** Let me clarify what exists:\n\n1. Backend: `CourseService.getTodayMilestones(teacherId)` - this method queries CourseStudentModel to find courses where:\n   - `course.start_date` = today AND `course.status = 'draft'` → opening courses\n   - `course.end_date` = today AND `course.status = 'ongoing'` → closing courses\n   \n3. Frontend: `CourseMilestoneBanner` calls this API to fetch the data and display the banner\n\nSo the real question is whether the `start_date` and `end_date` fields on courses actually have the correct values populated in the database. Since the user wants demo mode removed, I'll update the Dashboard component and walk them through how the detection logic works end-to-end.","thinkingSignature":"85b1aef3d34a26ac60ba1bc1c2b1ad24cebe363434c7d8e2dae80f14a3c9e7ff"},{"type":"text","text":"Có rồi! Logic đã implement đầy đủ ở backend. Mình gỡ demo mode:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_js509envop55_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/app/dashboard/Dashboard/Dashboard.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"      {/* Course Milestone Banner */}\n      <CourseMilestoneBanner demoMode />\n","newText":"      {/* Course Milestone Banner (teacher only) */}\n      <CourseMilestoneBanner />\n"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":351,"cacheRead":124941,"cacheWrite":524,"totalTokens":125816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966447728,"responseId":"06398e31e17fca5