{"type":"message","id":"c35f2ff6","parentId":"a8f2f771","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:54:34.030Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"6140\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"sender\": \"Khuong\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-23 17:51 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Khuong (6053576134)\",\n  \"id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"Khuong\",\n  \"username\": \"khuowgn\"\n}\n```\n\n1. đúng rồi, 2. Trường chỉ tiêu đã có bạn vào backend xem model, 3. Form thêm kỳ thi tốt nghiệp, kỳ thi sát hạch"}],"timestamp":1776966873938}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e04affa","parentId":"c35f2ff6","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:54:48.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context. Let me understand the 3 tasks clearly:\n\n1. **Chặn ngày kết thúc < ngày bắt đầu**: In course form, validate that end_date >= start_date.\n\n2. **Giới hạn số lượng học viên <= chỉ tiêu**: When assigning students to a course, check `course.max_students` (field exists in model: `max_students?: number`) against current `student_count`. If `current + new > max_students`, show error.\n\n3. **Form thêm đợt thi - validate khi bấm thông báo lần 1**: The user is saying that when creating an exam batch (sát hạch or tốt nghiệp), when they click \"Thông báo lần 1\" (notification round 1), there should be validation. But looking at the code, the ExamModal and AddGraduationExamModal are for creating exam batches - they don't have a \"thông báo lần 1\" button.\n   \nI think I'm overcomplicating this. The user probably means that when creating an exam batch for sát hạch or tốt nghiệp, there are required fields like stadium location that need validation before the batch can be created or submitted for notification. Looking at the ExamModal component, I can see it already validates required fields like name, plannedDate, venueId, and region, displaying error messages when these are missing. The validation function checks if the venueId field is empty and shows an appropriate error message if it hasn't been filled in yet.\n\nSo the pattern is clear—when a field fails validation, an error message appears below it, and once the user corrects it and the field is no longer empty, that error message disappears. The user is essentially asking me to implement this same validation behavior for exam batch creation, specifically ensuring required fields are filled before attempting to create or submit the batch.\n\nNow I need to create a task list and start working through the three main features: adding end date validation to the course form, implementing student limit enforcement in the assignment flow, and then applying this same validation pattern to the exam batch creation forms.\n\nLet me start by checking out to a new branch to keep these changes organized.","thinkingSignature":"b5a14d35b79a21604688c86430b71fc470250fd9ac40281d029743d03ec27160"},{"type":"text","text":"Mình đã hiểu đủ context. Bắt đầu làm 3 task. Checkout branch mới trước.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h6wbhcfvoj2r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be && git checkout -b fix/course-date-validation-max-students-20260423 && git checkout -b fix/exam-batch-required-validation-20260423 2>/dev/null; git branch --show-current","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":625,"cacheRead":10391,"cacheWrite":27033,"totalTokens":38049,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966874030,"responseId":"06398fdb431e2614e81ca2faeb4b6ef2"}}
