{"type":"message","id":"d8371221","parentId":"0dfa3f41","timestamp":"2026-04-23T17:55:51.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have enough context to implement all 3 tasks. Let me do them one by one.\n\n**Task 1**: Add end_date >= start_date validation in AddCourseModal.tsx\n\n**Task 2**: Add max_students limit check in both FE (courses/page.tsx) and BE (course.service.ts)\n\n**Task 3**: The form validation already works correctly (error shows when field is empty, clears when field is filled). But let me double check the FieldWrapper component to make sure the error display is correct.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirement:\n\"3. ở trong form thêm đợt thi tốt nghiệp, thi sát hạch khi thông báo lần 1 là thiếu trường như (sân thi) sau khi chọn lại rồi thì phải ẩn thông báo đó đi\"\n\n\nFor the exam batch forms, the validation logic is already working—when a user selects a stadium and triggers the change handler, it updates the form state and marks the field as touched, which then runs validation and clears the error message if the field is now filled. Task 3 is already complete. Let me verify this is functioning correctly by checking the FieldWrapper implementation.\n\nFor Task 3, I should confirm that the error display disappears once the user selects a stadium. Looking at the FieldWrapper component, it conditionally renders the error message only when the field has been touched and there's an error, so when the form state updates after selection, the error should hide automatically. I think the issue might be that Task 3 is actually asking for validation when a \"Thông báo lần 1\" button is clicked, not just on field selection. But since I can't find this button anywhere, the user probably just wants to ensure the existing validation is working properly—where errors display for empty required fields and clear once the fields are filled. Let me verify this behavior is already in place and move forward with implementing Tasks 1 and 2.\n\nFor Task 2, I need to check the `max_students` limit both client-side when the user assigns students and server-side in the course service. Looking at the courses page, I can see where the student count is displayed, so I'll need to access the `max_students` value from the selected course and validate against it before allowing assignment.\n\nOn the backend, the `assignStudentsToCourse` method needs to query the course document to get its `max_students` limit and current enrollment count, then reject the assignment if adding the new students would exceed that threshold.\n\nImplementing the field validation now...","thinkingSignature":"933b163a166d742abd0793f952012b7d8ed0ae125b5341b1e4a0c3d6e9b4d916"},{"type":"text","text":"Đủ context rồi. Mình implement luôn 3 tasks:\n\n**Task 3** đã hoạt động đúng — lỗi hiện khi thiếu, ẩn khi điền. Mình verify nhanh.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1w9o0y7yuzdk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"hasError\\|errors\\[field\\]\\|touched\\[field\\]\" src/components/sat-hach/ExamModal.tsx | head -10","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":436,"output":727,"cacheRead":42148,"cacheWrite":1216,"totalTokens":44527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776966937442,"responseId":"0639901ac8b708af36e5de23a3aba29c"}}
