{"type":"message","id":"69799d67","parentId":"953d02f5","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:09:22.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the data:\n- Overdue draft (should be ongoing): 1 course\n- Overdue ongoing (should be completed): 13 courses\n- Opening today: 2 courses\n- Closing today: 0 courses\n\nSo the fix to use `courses` collection name should work. Let me also check if the teacher_id in coursestudents matches the teacher's user._id. Let me also verify what the `coursestudents` collection has.\n\nWait, there's an issue. The `getTodayMilestones` queries `CourseStudentModel` first (matches `teacher_id`), then does $lookup to `courses`. The `teacher_id` in `coursestudents` should match the teacher's `_id` in the `users` collection. \n\nI need to verify that the teachers have the right `_id` values and that these are actually stored as ObjectId in the `coursestudents` collection.","thinkingSignature":"ea788119ae9e8555cb9dadb8a5c13a00ed3631231a02b5e457dbc244c4df928d"},{"type":"text","text":"Database có 1 draft quá hạn + 13 ongoing quá hạn + 2 mở hôm nay. Fix `courseinfos` → `courses` là đúng. Commit:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4nw73wg6oa99_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"fix: milestones used wrong collection name 'courseinfos' (should be 'courses')\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":262,"output":333,"cacheRead":67535,"cacheWrite":829,"totalTokens":68959,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776967754118,"responseId":"0639934b3eeb839b257ffdd12d793188"}}
