{"type":"message","id":"43585a81","parentId":"756e5e2e","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:09:54.769Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `role` field is `undefined` in all users! This means the `users` collection doesn't have a `role` field - it's likely stored in a separate collection called `userroles`. \n\nThe `teacher_id` in `coursestudents` points to the `_id` in the `users` collection directly. The user `teacher@qlhv.vn` has `_id: 69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e` which IS the `teacher_id` in `coursestudents`. But this user doesn't have a `role` field in `users` collection.\n\nLet me check `userroles` collection.","thinkingSignature":"208c3bf47df7c3bf8357d006023cb8bf171391a888902809f47d4966d6449a60"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6l5vx8rbd9ae_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://root:RYLoQJqsDr4EQIJB@103.253.21.98:27017/dtlx?authSource=admin\" --quiet --eval '\n// Check userroles collection\nvar ur = db.userroles.find({}).toArray();\nprint(\"userroles count: \" + ur.length);\nur.slice(0, 5).forEach(function(u) { printjson(u); });\n\n// Check structure of users collection\nvar sampleUser = db.users.findOne({ username: \"teacher@qlhv.vn\" });\nprint(\"\\nTeacher user structure:\");\nObject.keys(sampleUser).forEach(function(k) { print(\"  \" + k + \": \" + JSON.stringify(sampleUser[k])); });\n'\n","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":204,"output":335,"cacheRead":68960,"cacheWrite":1794,"totalTokens":71293,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776967787518,"responseId":"0639936df4dad2d0b28f40dd3aff911a"}}
