{"type":"message","id":"6bca4953","parentId":"1d6a21dd","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:10:13.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the data model:\n- `users` collection: has `_id` but no `role` field\n- `userroles` collection: maps `user_id` to `role_id`\n- `roles` collection: has role names\n\nSo to check if a user is a teacher, you need to join `users` → `userroles` → `roles`. The `_id` in `users` is a STRING (not ObjectId), while the `user_id` in `userroles` is an ObjectId.\n\nThe teacher's `_id` in `users` is `\"69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e\"` (string), but `userroles.user_id` is `ObjectId('69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e')`.\n \nThe real problem is that when the `getTodayMilestones` API receives a token with the user's ID, it's not properly checking if that user is actually a teacher through the roles table. Looking at the backend code, it queries `CourseStudentModel` filtering by `teacher_id` as an ObjectId, but the `teacher_id` values in the database might not match the format being passed in, or the role verification itself is broken.\n\nSince the milestone banner only displays when `role === 'teacher'`, if that check is failing, the banner won't show at all. The user mentioned seeing no badge but didn't clarify whether the banner itself is visible. I need to verify what the JWT token's user object actually contains and whether the role check is even working correctly.\n\nLooking at the `getTodayMilestones` query, the issue is that it's trying to match a string `teacherId` directly against ObjectIds in the `teacher_id` field, which won't work unless they're the same type. Plus, the current query only looks for courses starting today, but the user also wants to see courses that already passed their start date but are still marked as drafts.\n\nI've fixed the collection name, but now I'm wondering if the `teacher_id` field in `coursestudents` actually stores teacher IDs or student IDs—the name is ambiguous. Let me trace through the relationship: if a course has many students enrolled through `coursestudents`, each record links a `student_id` to a `course_id`, but the `teacher_id` field suggests each enrollment might also be assigned to a specific teacher.\n\nNow I need to verify whether the current user (logged in as a teacher) is actually appearing in the `coursestudents` records with matching `teacher_id` values, or if there's a type mismatch preventing the query from returning results.","thinkingSignature":"6b72d876b3daa66eca6aeb49455e381ca7bceb84e49ba4ee7e91aa66fe0db3ab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j0gcb9v9khfa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://root:RYLoQJqsDr4EQIJB@103.253.21.98:27017/dtlx?authSource=admin\" --quiet --eval '\n// Check what the teacher@qlhv.vn user _id is\nvar teacherUser = db.users.findOne({ username: \"teacher@qlhv.vn\" });\nprint(\"Teacher user _id: \" + teacherUser._id + \" (type: \" + typeof teacherUser._id + \")\");\n\n// Check if coursestudents has records for this teacher\nvar teacherCsCount = db.coursestudents.countDocuments({ teacher_id: ObjectId.createFromHexString(teacherUser._id.substring(0,24)) });\nprint(\"coursestudents for this teacher: \" + teacherCsCount);\n\n// Check if courses linked to this teacher have milestone-worthy dates\nvar courses = db.coursestudents.aggregate([\n  { $match: { teacher_id: ObjectId.createFromHexString(teacherUser._id.substring(0,24)) } },\n  { $lookup: { from: \"courses\", localField: \"course_id\", foreignField: \"_id\", as: \"course\" } },\n  { $unwind: \"$course\" },\n  { $match: { \"course.status\": { $in: [\"draft\", \"ongoing\"] } } },\n  { $project: { name: \"$course.name\", start_date: \"$course.start_date\", end_date: \"$course.end_date\", status: \"$course.status\" } }\n]).toArray();\nprint(\"\\nCourses for this teacher with draft/ongoing:\");\ncourses.forEach(function(c) {\n  print(\"  [\" + c.status + \"] \" + c.name + \" | start: \" + (c.start_date ? new Date(c.start_date).toISOString().split(\"T\")[0] : \"null\") + \" | end: \" + (c.end_date ? new Date(c.end_date).toISOString().split(\"T\")[0] : \"null\"));\n});\n'\n","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":764,"output":1006,"cacheRead":70317,"cacheWrite":917,"totalTokens":73004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776967795980,"responseId":"063993757ff68a4075bfb0f7c653c079"}}
