{"type":"message","id":"591f9a98","parentId":"984b7d31","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:13:22.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the users but can't log in as teacher. Let me try to login as admin to get a token, then check the milestones API.\n\nActually, the user is saying they logged in but can't see the banner. This means the BE is returning some data but the banner isn't showing. Let me think about what could be going wrong.\n\nPossible issues:\n1. The user is not logging in as a teacher (role check fails)\n2. The API returns empty data\n3. The frontend role check fails\n\nLet me ask the user to check their localStorage user role, or let me try logging in as admin to test the API.Actually, let me just try logging in as admin to get a valid token.","thinkingSignature":"2d0a5025223b950262581812e5f441002d343ee0b4d03bbadfc9cf7ffc12991d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s3jo1gi7j8pp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Login as admin to test the API\nRESULT=$(curl -s -X POST http://localhost:5002/api/v1/auth/login \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"admin@qlhv.vn\",\"password\":\"admin123\"}')\nTOKEN=$(echo $RESULT | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('token',''))\" 2>/dev/null)\necho \"Token: $(echo $TOKEN | cut -c1-40)...\"\necho \"---\"\n# Call milestones with teacher_id of teacher@qlhv.vn\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:5002/api/v1/courses/today-milestones?teacher_id=69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":339,"output":374,"cacheRead":94202,"cacheWrite":566,"totalTokens":95481,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776967993837,"responseId":"0639943b4dd6aa0553c360196608994d"}}
