{"type":"message","id":"bbf4f433","parentId":"85e96829","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:14:31.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `getTodayMilestones` controller gets the teacher ID from `user.id` in the JWT. Let me look at what the user object looks like when I login as admin. Admin has `role: \"superadmin\"`, not teacher. So when admin logs in, `user.id` is the admin's ID, and the milestones query would look for `teacher_id = admin_id` in `coursestudents`, which returns nothing.\n\nLet me check: what does the `user.id` look like when admin logs in? And what does the controller use?Let me look at the JWT decode and the controller more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"83f6825c8a202fab570cf5a3ffb16f2ee9907935de75d451f3e658250703c41a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k6tlv5px34rt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport urllib.request, json, base64\n\nlogin_data = json.dumps({\"username\": \"admin@qlhv.vn\", \"password\": \"admin123\"}).encode()\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\"http://localhost:5002/api/v1/auth/login\", data=login_data, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"})\nres = urllib.request.urlopen(req)\nlogin_result = json.loads(res.read())\ntoken = login_result[\"data\"][\"token\"]\n\n# Decode JWT payload\npayload = token.split(\".\")[1] + \"==\"\ndecoded = base64.b64decode(payload).decode()\nprint(\"JWT payload:\", decoded)\n\n# So when admin logs in, user.id = \"69e8333ddbb6750f8166f057\"\n# The query looks for coursestudents with teacher_id = admin's ObjectId\n# That won't match any records since admin isn't a teacher\n# Let me test with the actual teacher's token\n\n# Login as a teacher user - but we don't know the password\n# Let me check if there's a teacher user we can reset password for\nprint(\"\\nTeacher user _id from DB: 69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e\")\nPYEOF","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","u