{"type":"message","id":"798ec7c7","parentId":"16384291","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:16:58.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user still can't see the banner even after logging in as teacher. Let me think about what could be wrong:\n\n1. The API is returning data correctly (1048 overdue closing courses) when logged in as teacher\n2. But the banner isn't showing\n\nPossible issues:\n1. The frontend isn't fetching the data correctly\n2. The frontend is checking `role === 'teacher'` but the user's role in localStorage might be different\n3. The user might be logging in as a different account\n\nLet me check the frontend code to see how the user role is determined and how the banner visibility is checked.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The frontend stores the user in localStorage. When the user logs in, the JWT token contains the role. But the frontend banner check reads from `localStorage.getItem('user')` and checks `user.role`. \n\n\nI need to verify what role is actually being stored in localStorage when the user logs in—it might not be 'teacher' even though the backend has that role assigned. I should also confirm whether the FE dev server is actually running, since the user mentioned restarting their local environment.","thinkingSignature":"bc9f69fc512ca4268bc7888fd94c40072f6e0aa0c221f4a9d331f892540e74da"},{"type":"text","text":"Mình debug trực tiếp xem FE đang làm gì.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_738dtw5wlldq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"next dev.*ahv-qlhv\" | grep -v grep","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":318,"cacheRead":98791,"cacheWrite":17344,"totalTokens":116453,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968207266,"responseId":"06399511eaf42c543afad8e37bc069d6"}}
