{"type":"message","id":"53c777b0","parentId":"c47736e9","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:18:30.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `useEffect` has `[demoMode]` as dependency, but now it also uses `user` (from the hook). Since `user` is from a hook and doesn't change within the effect itself, this should be fine. The effect will re-run when `demoMode` changes, and on each run it checks the current `user`. This is correct behavior.\n\nBut actually, there might be a timing issue - when the component first mounts, `user` might be null initially (before the token is read from localStorage and the user is set). When the user object is loaded (from token), the effect won't re-run because `demoMode` hasn't changed.\n\nLet me add `user` to the dependency array so the effect re-runs when user is loaded.","thinkingSignature":"ee0ce521680873a47fabbc09662f428ccde32fa22126ef7aa5bf4d37d9b53810"},{"type":"text","text":"Cần thêm `user` vào dependency array để effect chạy lại khi user được load:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_94vk7n5qzs6o_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe/src/components/dashboard/CourseMilestoneBanner.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"  }, [demoMode]);","newText":"  }, [demoMode, user]);"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":83,"output":270,"cacheRead":119324,"cacheWrite":376,"totalTokens":120053,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968302721,"responseId":"063995702813a82a9170f42622c15b09"}}
