{"type":"message","id":"58d3f9c1","parentId":"ef46f1ce","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:18:39.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, if `user` is null initially, then when the effect runs with `user = null`, `setLoading(false)` will be called and the banner won't show. Then when the user logs in and `user` becomes non-null, the effect will re-run and fetch milestones. This is the correct behavior.\n\nBut actually, `user` in the dependency array might cause an issue because the `user` object reference changes on every render if it's not memoized. This could cause the effect to run too often.\n\nActually, looking at the AuthContext, `user` state is set with `setUser(userData)` which creates a new object each time. So every time the user state changes (even to the same value), the component re-renders and `user` reference changes. This could cause the effect to run very often.\n\n\nThe Dashboard component probably doesn't re-render frequently though, so this should be manageable. I think the better approach is to use the `useAuth` hook's `loading` state to wait until the user is actually authenticated before running the effect.","thinkingSignature":"ed9270ea68d4594207b3fba8865c6af4544f9a2925bcc638ba35d1546377d6e6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wxsrmfxikwk4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"loading\\|setLoading\" src/context/AuthContext.tsx | head -10","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":312,"cacheRead":119558,"cacheWrite":436,"totalTokens":120416,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968310633,"responseId":"0639957871e7c8188eddaf2f67accba6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f26c5d2","parentId":"58d3f9c1","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:18:39.463Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wxsrmfxikwk4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"27:  loading: boolean;\n35:  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n63:        setLoading(false);\n74:        setLoading(false);\n101:        if (newToken && userData) setLoading(false);\n106:      loading,\n108:    [token, user, refreshUser, loading],"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"27:  loading: boolean;\n35:  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n63:        setLoading(false);\n74:        setLoading(false);\n101:        if (newToken && userData) setLoading(false);\n106:      loading,\n108:    [token, user, refreshUser, loading],","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776968319456}}
{"type":"message","id":"11698b5e","parentId":"6f26c5d2","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:18:47.425Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a `loading` state in AuthContext. I should use it to avoid the dependency issue. Let me update the banner to use `authLoading` and `user` from AuthContext, and skip when still loading.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. The simplest and most correct fix: use `useAuth()` to get `user`, skip when `loading` is true, and only check the role when `user` is available. The dependency array should include `user` so that when the user logs in and `user` becomes non-null, the effect re-runs.\n\nBut the issue with `user` as a dependency is that if the user object is recreated on every render (not memoized), it would cause the effect to run on every render. \n\nSince the `user` from AuthContext is just a state variable that only changes when the auth state actually changes, the effect running on those occasions is fine. I think this approach will work well. Let me go ahead and commit this fix, then test it out.","thinkingSignature":"31f8062911dc0b1d9c89cbca002adf7864a5b583477e610f3838afbb998f1739"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_muxtjptf1khl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"fix: add user to useEffect dependency so banner loads after user auth\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":144,"output":309,"cacheRead":119719,"cacheWrite":638,"totalTokens":120810,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968319475,"responseId":"063995812a0b06f0e0c6f3025e0e2ed0"}}
