{"type":"message","id":"bfaab041","parentId":"8d96bbed","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:21:08.995Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HEE draft course is assigned to teacher `lihn123`, not the current teacher `teacher@qlhv.vn`. So the current teacher won't see it.\n\nBut there's another teacher account `lihn123` that we could use. But we already set `teacher123` password for `teacher@qlhv.vn`.\n\nThe issue here is that the current teacher account (`teacher@qlhv.vn`) doesn't have any draft courses that are overdue. The overdue draft course (HEE) is assigned to another teacher (`lihn123`).\n\nBut the user says they can't see overdue draft courses. Let me think about what the user means...\n\nActually, the user might be using a different teacher account (maybe `lihn123`) and expecting to see overdue draft courses. Let me suggest that the user should:\n\n\n1. Use the account `lihn123` to see the HEE draft course\n2. Or I could create a test draft course assigned to the current teacher\n\nOR, the user might be asking for ALL draft courses in the system to show, not just those assigned to the teacher. But that doesn't make sense for a teacher-specific banner.\n\nWait, let me reconsider what the user is actually saying. They want courses from previous days that haven't been updated to appear in the notification too. This likely refers to courses in ongoing status where the end date has already passed but the course hasn't been marked as completed yet.\n\nThe teacher should definitely see those kinds of overdue courses. Let me double-check the API response more carefully to see if I'm missing something about what's being returned. Let me get the unique courses:","thinkingSignature":"c3af9e0ec36ee2931e3d62e8fc4ed08ac32ca9f2edd53c3964ffec669193c56f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8fwd3f2by24s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport urllib.request, json\n\nlogin_data = json.dumps({\"username\": \"teacher@qlhv.vn\", \"password\": \"teacher123\"}).encode()\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\"http://localhost:5002/api/v1/auth/login\", data=login_data, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"})\nres = urllib.request.urlopen(req)\ntoken = json.loads(res.read())[\"data\"][\"token\"]\n\nmilestone_req = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:5002/api/v1/courses/today-milestones\",\n    headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {token}\"}\n)\nmilestone_res = urllib.request.urlopen(milestone_req)\nresult = json.loads(milestone_res.read())\nd = result[\"data\"]\n\n# Deduplicate by course _id\nseen = set()\nunique_closing = []\nfor c in d[\"closingCourses\"]:\n    if c[\"_id\"] not in seen:\n        seen.add(c[\"_id\"])\n        unique_closing.append(c)\n\nprint(f\"Total (with dupes): {len(d['closingCourses'])}\")\nprint(f\"Unique closing courses: {len(unique_closing)}\")\nprint(f\"overdueClosingCount: {d['overdueClosingCount']}\")\nprint(f\"Unique overdue closing courses:\")\nfor c in unique_closing[:10]:\n    print(f\"  [{c['status']}] {c['name']} | end: {c['end_date']}\")\nprint(f\"\\nUnique draft courses (overdue opening):\")\nprint(f\"  overdueOpeningCount: {d['overdueOpeningCount']}\")\nPYEOF","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":105,"output":716,"cacheRead":120895,"cacheWrite":1331,"totalTokens":123047,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968455909,"responseId":"063996098b95860c92ba46a4a76685e8"}}
