{"type":"message","id":"1db8dc7c","parentId":"ba585e00","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:25:16.230Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! Course A11 (khóa test22/4) has:\n- status: draft (Sắp khai giảng)\n- start_date: 2026-04-23 (today)\n- teacher_id: null\n\nThe problem is that this course has `teacher_id: null` in the coursestudents table. So when we query for `teacher_id = teacherOid`, it doesn't match this course.\n\nThe fix is to also show milestones for courses where the teacher_id is null. Or better - the user should be able to see all draft/ongoing courses that have no specific teacher assigned.\n\nWait, but this is a design question. Should the milestone banner show courses with `teacher_id = null` to all teachers? Or should it only show courses assigned to the specific teacher?\n\n\nThe user seems to expect that `teacher@qlhv.vn` should see the A11 course even though it has `teacher_id: null`, which suggests courses with no specific teacher should be visible to all teachers. This might actually be a feature gap rather than a bug. I need to check how the milestone API is being called from the frontend to understand what's actually being queried.","thinkingSignature":"d287b12b42787198afdc603b573af402abe9c1d860c53a4d0fe57e6dd4eb4338"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm thấy rồi! Khóa A11 có `teacher_id: null` — không gán cho ai cả. Mình cập nhật query để tài khoản teacher thấy được khóa không gán giáo viên:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c1vqgxytbf5t_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/course.service.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"    // Base pipeline to get teacher's courses with student count\n    const basePipeline = (matchStage: any) => [\n      { $match: { teacher_id: teacherOid } },\n      {","newText":"    // Base pipeline: match courses assigned to this teacher OR courses with no teacher assigned\n    // This ensures teachers see milestone notifications for unassigned courses too\n    const basePipeline = (matchStage: any) => [\n      { $match: { $or: [{ teacher_id: teacherOid }, { teacher_id: null }] } },\n      {"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":495,"cacheRead":128010,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128505,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968705157,"responseId":"063997021d8d1f05b1994b3cb256c843"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab710116","parentId":"1db8dc7c","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:25:16.291Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c1vqgxytbf5t_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/course.service.ts."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 243     today.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n 244     const tomorrow = new Date(today);\n 245     tomorrow.setDate(tomorrow.getDate() + 1);\n 246 \n-247     // Base pipeline to get teacher's courses with student count\n+247     // Base pipeline: match courses assigned to this teacher OR courses with no teacher assigned\n+248     // This ensures teachers see milestone notifications for unassigned courses too\n 248     const basePipeline = (matchStage: any) => [\n-249       { $match: { teacher_id: teacherOid } },\n+250       { $match: { $or: [{ teacher_id: teacherOid }, { teacher_id: null }] } },\n 250       {\n 251         $lookup: {\n 252           from: 'courses',\n 253           localField: 'course_id',\n     ...","firstChangedLine":247},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776968716267}}
{"type":"message","id":"37923c4b","parentId":"ab710116","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:25:28.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, this is a bit tricky. The `$lookup` for `course` happens AFTER the `$match` on `teacher_id`. If teacher_id is null, the match `{ $or: [{ teacher_id: teacherOid }, { teacher_id: null }] }` would include records with teacher_id = null. But `teacherOid` is a mongoose ObjectId, and null is null - they should match correctly.\n\nBut actually, there might be another issue. If teacher_id in coursestudents is `null`, then the `$or` match `{ teacher_id: teacherOid }` won't match the ObjectId against null. And `{ teacher_id: null }` might not work if the field doesn't exist or is stored as something else.\n\n\nLet me verify what the actual data looks like - the previous query showed teacher_id as null for some records, so the `$or` condition should catch both the matched ObjectId and null values. I'm realizing the issue might be how MongoDB handles querying for null values across different scenarios. Let me just test this directly with mongosh to see what's actually happening when I query for courses where teacher_id is null.","thinkingSignature":"f996370457504167f9becc01c9eb209bd0c66090bd0de9540ac41e70570c150d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7sugmxq4qbhs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://root:RYLoQJqsDr4EQIJB@103.253.21.98:27017/dtlx?authSource=admin\" --quiet --eval '\nvar teacherOid = ObjectId(\"69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e\");\nvar today = new Date();\ntoday.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n\n// Test: match courses for teacher OR with null teacher\nvar test = db.coursestudents.aggregate([\n  { $match: { $or: [{ teacher_id: teacherOid }, { teacher_id: null }] } },\n  { $lookup: { from: \"courses\", localField: \"course_id\", foreignField: \"_id\", as: \"course\" } },\n  { $unwind: \"$course\" },\n  { $match: { \"course.status\": \"draft\", \"course.start_date\": { $lt: today } } },\n  { $project: { name: \"$course.name\", code: \"$course.code\", start_date: \"$course.start_date\", teacher_id: 1, status: \"$course.status\" } },\n  { $limit: 5 }\n]).toArray();\nprint(\"Overdue draft courses for teacher (including null teacher):\");\nif (test.length === 0) print(\"  (none)\");\ntest.forEach(function(c) {\n  print(\"  \" + c.code + \" | \" + c.name + \" | start: \" + (c.start_date ? new Date(c.start_date).toISOString().split(\"T\")[0] : \"null\") + \" | teacher_id: \" + c.teacher_id);\n});\n'\n","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":106,"output":627,"cacheRead":127241,"cacheWrite":1205,"totalTokens":129179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968716351,"responseId":"0639970e7248092f2ed072ed7e4b820b"}}
