{"type":"message","id":"9aa2164a","parentId":"9799b13a","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:26:17.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but this creates another issue: \"opening today\" (start_date >= today AND start_date < tomorrow) vs \"overdue opening\" (start_date <= today, draft). With A11 having start_date exactly at midnight today:- \"opening today\" query: `start_date >= today AND start_date < tomorrow` = true\n- \"overdue opening\" query: `start_date <= today AND status = draft` = true\n\nSo A11 will appear in BOTH \"opening today\" AND \"overdue opening\". This is fine actually - the user will see it with the overdue badge. But the counts might be slightly confusing.\n\nActually, the better approach is: the \"overdue\" query should be `start_date < today` for truly overdue, and the \"opening today\" query should handle courses starting today. But the user specifically wants to see courses that \"passed their KG date but not updated\" to be in overdue. A course with start_date exactly today should be treated as overdue if not updated by the teacher (since it's already 18:24 on that day).\n\n\nLet me verify this approach works with the test data to make sure the logic is sound.","thinkingSignature":"a27d306e84c813e97e8e38ffed1823f21a18035b944e68d15239da9efd83838a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4c29bkqm28a8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://root:RYLoQJqsDr4EQIJB@103.253.21.98:27017/dtlx?authSource=admin\" --quiet --eval '\nvar teacherOid = ObjectId(\"69e8333ddbb6750f8166f05e\");\nvar today = new Date();\ntoday.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n\n// Test with $lte for overdue\nvar overdueOpening = db.coursestudents.aggregate([\n  { $match: { $or: [{ teacher_id: teacherOid }, { teacher_id: null }] } },\n  { $lookup: { from: \"courses\", localField: \"course_id\", foreignField: \"_id\", as: \"course\" } },\n  { $unwind: \"$course\" },\n  { $match: { \"course.start_date\": { $lte: today }, \"course.status\": \"draft\" } },\n  { $project: { name: \"$course.name\", code: \"$course.code\", start_date: \"$course.start_date\" } },\n  { $group: { _id: \"$course._id\", name: { $first: \"$course.name\" }, code: { $first: \"$course.code\" }, start_date: { $first: \"$course.start_date\" } } }\n]).toArray();\nprint(\"Overdue opening courses (draft + start_date <= today):\");\nif (overdueOpening.length === 0) print(\"  (none)\");\noverdueOpening.forEach(function(c) {\n  var sd = c.start_date ? new Date(c.start_date).toISOString().split(\"T\")[0] : \"null\";\n  print(\"  \" + c.code + \" | \" + c.name + \" | start: \" + sd);\n});\n'\n","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":106,"output":661,"cacheRead":129145,"cacheWrite":2459,"totalTokens":132371,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968765008,"responseId":"0639973e30ce9b386d43779551f9192b"}}
