{"type":"message","id":"248c6041","parentId":"a7d48f07","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:27:35.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to fix the overdue queries so they don't include courses that are already in the \"today\" queries. The overdueOpening should exclude courses that start today (those are in the \"opening today\" query).Similarly for overdueClosing.\n\nLet me update the overdue queries to add an additional condition: `course.start_date < today` for overdueOpening (not `<= today`) and `course.end_date < today` for overdueClosing. This way:\n- Courses starting today → \"khai giảng hôm nay\"\n- Courses starting < today but draft → \"quá hạn khai giảng\"\n- Courses ending today → \"kết thúc hôm nay\"\n\n\n- Courses ending < today but ongoing → \"quá hạn kết thúc\"\n\nBut wait—the user specifically mentioned that A11, which started today, isn't showing up. The real issue might be timezone handling. The frontend is likely treating \"today\" as the local timezone (Vietnam is UTC+7), while the database stores dates in UTC. So when a course is created with start_date = \"2026-04-23\" in local time, it gets stored as something like \"2026-04-22T17:00:00.000Z\" in UTC, which falls before the query's today threshold.\n\nThe fix using `$lte: today` should catch these cases. However, this creates a duplicate—if A11 starts today, it appears in both \"khai giảng hôm nay\" and \"quá hạn\", which is confusing. I need to make the overdue query exclude courses that start today by changing it from `$lte: today` to `$lt: today`, but that might reintroduce the original problem. Looking at the current output showing `openingCount: 4` with only 1 unique course, it seems the counts might already be deduplicated, so let me verify what's actually being returned. I'm realizing the counts might include duplicates from multiple records, while the course arrays are deduplicated. The safest approach is to switch back to `$lt: today` for overdue queries and handle timezone conversion in the code instead, so \"today\" actually represents the user's local date rather than UTC midnight. The user wants courses that have passed their start date but are still in draft status to show as overdue openings, so I need to change the comparison from `$lt: today` to `$lte: today` and then deduplicate across both categories using course IDs.","thinkingSignature":"6cf34903de7888bd204ca9689507b04083abc2707d00c59881f1c3f1deb95839"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9hc3bcuak90u_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/course.service.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"    return {\n      openingCourses: [...openingToday, ...overdueOpening],\n      closingCourses: [...closingToday, ...overdueClosing],\n      openingCount: openingToday.length + overdueOpening.length,\n      closingCount: closingToday.length + overdueClosing.length,\n      overdueOpeningCount: overdueOpening.length,\n      overdueClosingCount: overdueClosing.length,\n    };\n  }","newText":"    // Deduplicate by course _id to avoid showing same course in both \"today\" and \"overdue\" tabs\n    const seenOpening = new Set<string>();\n    const openingCourses = [...openingToday, ...overdueOpening].filter((c) => {\n      const id = (c._id as any).toString();\n      if (seenOpening.has(id)) return false;\n      seenOpening.add(id);\n      return true;\n    });\n\n    const seenClosing = new Set<string>();\n    const closingCourses = [...closingToday, ...overdueClosing].filter((c) => {\n      const id = (c._id as any).toString();\n      if (seenClosing.has(id)) return false;\n      seenClosing.add(id);\n      return true;\n    });\n\n    return {\n      openingCourses,\n      closingCourses,\n      openingCount: openingCourses.length,\n      closingCount: closingCourses.length,\n      overdueOpeningCount: overdueOpening.length,\n      overdueClosingCount: overdueClosing.length,\n    };\n  }"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":209,"output":902,"cacheRead":133214,"cacheWrite":1199,"totalTokens":135524,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968838466,"responseId":"06399788ee87e1a17e1780fd81a1f790"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4715b329","parentId":"248c6041","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:27:35.664Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9hc3bcuak90u_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/course.service.ts."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 301         'course.status': 'ongoing',\n 302       })\n 303     );\n 304 \n+305     // Deduplicate by course _id to avoid showing same course in both \"today\" and \"overdue\" tabs\n+306     const seenOpening = new Set<string>();\n+307     const openingCourses = [...openingToday, ...overdueOpening].filter((c) => {\n+308       const id = (c._id as any).toString();\n+309       if (seenOpening.has(id)) return false;\n+310       seenOpening.add(id);\n+311       return true;\n+312     });\n+313 \n+314     const seenClosing = new Set<string>();\n+315     const closingCourses = [...closingToday, ...overdueClosing].filter((c) => {\n+316       const id = (c._id as any).toString();\n+317       if (seenClosing.has(id)) return false;\n+318       seenClosing.add(id);\n+319       return true;\n+320     });\n+321 \n 305     return {\n-306       openingCourses: [...openingToday, ...overdueOpening],\n-307       closingCourses: [...closingToday, ...overdueClosing],\n-308       openingCount: openingToday.length + overdueOpening.length,\n-309       closingCount: closingToday.length + overdueClosing.length,\n+323       openingCourses,\n+324       closingCourses,\n+325       openingCount: openingCourses.length,\n+326       closingCount: closingCourses.length,\n 310       overdueOpeningCount: overdueOpening.length,\n 311       overdueClosingCount: overdueClosing.length,\n 312     };\n 313   }\n     ...","firstChangedLine":305},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776968855622}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfd1b8ff","parentId":"4715b329","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:27:49.525Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also update the FE banner to only show the badge for overdue if the course is in the overdue section (not the \"today\" section). But actually, with deduplication, courses starting today won't appear in the \"overdue\" list anymore. So the \"overdueOpeningCount\" will always be for courses with start_date < today.\n\nWait, but the user's complaint was \"khóa A11 có start_date = 2026-04-23 nhưng vẫn draft, tôi không thấy trong banner\". The issue was that A11 wasn't showing at all. With `$lte: today`, A11 now shows. But if A11 is in \"opening today\" (because start_date = today), and we deduplicate, it will show in \"opening today\" but NOT in \"overdue\". So `overdueOpeningCount` will be 0 for A11.\n \nThe badge only appears when a course falls strictly before today, so A11 won't get flagged as overdue since it's set to today. The user will see \"1 khóa khai giảng\" without any overdue badge, but that's what they need to act on. The frontend badge logic only increments when there are additional overdue courses beyond the opening count, so if A11 is the only course with start_date today, the badge stays hidden. For courses that started before today and are still draft, they'll appear in the overdue list instead. So the flow is: courses starting today show as a count without a badge, while courses past their start date but still draft appear separately with the badge to indicate they're overdue.\n\nNow I'm realizing the timing issue—if start_date is stored in UTC and today is calculated in local time, a course created today in Vietnam (UTC+7) might have a UTC date from yesterday, making it incorrectly appear overdue. Let me verify the timezone handling to make sure courses created today are properly categorized.","thinkingSignature":"ef816b2b9f25c10901adceaff096178d97674c98b0a60fa5b6cb974ee1678f02"},{"type":"text","text":"Commit and restart:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ne5esgaft6w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"fix: milestones query $lte for overdue + deduplicate course lists\n\n- overdueOpening/Closing use $lte: today (include courses starting/ending today)\n- Deduplicate by course _id to avoid showing same course in both today + overdue\n- Include courses with null teacher_id (unassigned courses)\n- Add overdue badge only when there are truly overdue courses beyond today\"\n","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":106,"output":563,"cacheRead":133788,"cacheWrite":1677,"totalTokens":136134,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968855734,"responseId":"06399799a7a3273dce5d7e577cc10be7"}}
