{"type":"message","id":"8f03f86c","parentId":"47c740d1","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:28:54.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but now the `overdueOpeningCount` and `overdueClosingCount` in the response are deduplicated (unique course counts). But the backend returns `openingCourses` which already includes all courses (today + overdue, deduplicated). So the FE will show all courses in one list.\n\nFor the badge, `overdueOpeningCount: 1` (unique overdue courses) and `openingCount: 1` (total unique khai giảng courses). The badge will show \"1 quá hạn\" but the course is ALSO in the main list. This creates visual redundancy.\n\nActually, I think the cleanest approach is:\n\n\n- Keep the combined `openingCourses` and `closingCourses` arrays that are fully deduplicated\n- Return the `overdueOpeningCount` and `overdueClosingCount` as unique counts for the badges\n- Display the overdue courses inline in the main list with a distinct visual treatment to differentiate them from today's courses","thinkingSignature":"c7d836b69d25691b49dd27a1ea32d3cced5ecd7b292c2dc8bd533deec8a2c3fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dj0xs1s8gh8x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"fix: deduplicate overdue counts to unique course IDs\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":106,"output":292,"cacheRead":136788,"cacheWrite":1072,"totalTokens":138258,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776968925561,"responseId":"063997df3233d29b3979e8dc71729b33"}}
