{"type":"message","id":"aa42802c","parentId":"1e94b9d9","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:38:10.543Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`gitlab-cli` was installed. But this might not be the same as `glab`. Let me check what was installed and try to configure GitLab access using the token from the remote URL.","thinkingSignature":"969ab4e0d9b83cf3df17e701c6cf03e9b0c6ed4a77da36dca755507fb9ddcaad"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_77qj5sqkfzta_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which gitlab-cli 2>/dev/null || npx gitlab-cli --version 2>/dev/null || echo \"checking...\"\n\n# Try to configure glab with the token from remote URL\nTOKEN=\"glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\"\ncurl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: $TOKEN\" \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/version\" | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -5","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":220,"output":207,"cacheRead":139538,"cacheWrite":370,"totalTokens":140335,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776969482561,"responseId":"06399a0c60a8f03cf1d79641920d94cb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b269e102","parentId":"aa42802c","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:38:14.780Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_77qj5sqkfzta_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: gitlab Action [Resource] [Options]\n\nResource:\n  Is the relative url to the ressource.\n\n  Examples:\n    foo/bar/issue for issues in the namespace 'foo' and the project 'bar'\n    foo/bar/issue/12 for issue with id 12 in namespace 'foo' and the project 'bar'\n\nActions:\n  get RESOURCE            Gets resource\n  list RESOURCE           Lists resource\n  create RESOURCE         Creates resource\n  remove RESOURCE         Deletes resource\n  update RESOURCE         Updates existing resource\n  close RESOURCE          Closes an issue\n  open RESOURCE           Opens an issue\n  comment RESOURCE        Comments an issue\n  alias RESOURCE ALIAS    Create a resource alias to prevent retyping long resource paths\n  rm-alias ALIAS          Removes an existing alias\n  list-aliases            Lists all aliases\n\nOptions:\n  -h --help                     Display this help\n  -m 'MESSAGE'                  Adds a message (first line will be treated as title other lines as body)\n  -u --user USERNAME            User to assign the issue to, default is \"me\" (use \"me\" to assign to user defined in environment)\n  -l --labels tag1,tag2         Comma separated list of labels\n  -f --filters key=value,...    Filter results by comma separated list of key=value pairs. Results must match these key=value pairs.\n  --json                        Output all data as JSON\n  --data key=value,...          Set data by comma separated list of key=value pairs.\n  --data-json JSON              Set data using a JSON string. If \"data\" is also set, it will overwrite existing keys.\n  --accept-certs                If present all SSL certificates (including self-signed) will be accepted\n  --config=path/to/config.js    Set path to configuration file to use. If not set it will look for the file in ~/.config/gitlab-cli/default.js\n  --debug                       If present will display debug information\nchecking...\n{\n    \"version\": \"19.0.0-pre\",\n    \"revision\": \"6a5c2dffbae\",\n    \"kas\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4204,"aggregated":"Usage: gitlab Action [Resource] [Options]\n\nResource:\n  Is the relative url to the ressource.\n\n  Examples:\n    foo/bar/issue for issues in the namespace 'foo' and the project 'bar'\n    foo/bar/issue/12 for issue with id 12 in namespace 'foo' and the project 'bar'\n\nActions:\n  get RESOURCE            Gets resource\n  list RESOURCE           Lists resource\n  create RESOURCE         Creates resource\n  remove RESOURCE         Deletes resource\n  update RESOURCE         Updates existing resource\n  close RESOURCE          Closes an issue\n  open RESOURCE           Opens an issue\n  comment RESOURCE        Comments an issue\n  alias RESOURCE ALIAS    Create a resource alias to prevent retyping long resource paths\n  rm-alias ALIAS          Removes an existing alias\n  list-aliases            Lists all aliases\n\nOptions:\n  -h --help                     Display this help\n  -m 'MESSAGE'                  Adds a message (first line will be treated as title other lines as body)\n  -u --user USERNAME            User to assign the issue to, default is \"me\" (use \"me\" to assign to user defined in environment)\n  -l --labels tag1,tag2         Comma separated list of labels\n  -f --filters key=value,...    Filter results by comma separated list of key=value pairs. Results must match these key=value pairs.\n  --json                        Output all data as JSON\n  --data key=value,...          Set data by comma separated list of key=value pairs.\n  --data-json JSON              Set data using a JSON string. If \"data\" is also set, it will overwrite existing keys.\n  --accept-certs                If present all SSL certificates (including self-signed) will be accepted\n  --config=path/to/config.js    Set path to configuration file to use. If not set it will look for the file in ~/.config/gitlab-cli/default.js\n  --debug                       If present will display debug information\nchecking...\n{\n    \"version\": \"19.0.0-pre\",\n    \"revision\": \"6a5c2dffbae\",\n    \"kas\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776969494772}}
{"type":"message","id":"11a36238","parentId":"b269e102","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:38:20.932Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the GitLab API is accessible with the token. Now let me figure out the best way to create MRs and wait for them to be merged.\n\nLet me first check what projects are available and then start the workflow.","thinkingSignature":"5082b26ef0418542da81e6df16667c28c64e51154169068876e098f5a7bfb15c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b27vcv0jpvgw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=\"glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\"\ncurl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: $TOKEN\" \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects?search=ahv-qlhv\" | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nprojects = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor p in projects:\n    print(f'  {p[\\\"id\\\"]} | {p[\\\"path_with_namespace\\\"]}')\n\"","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":532,"output":213,"cacheRead":139778,"cacheWrite":498,"totalTokens":141021,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776969494796,"responseId":"06399a18a06364fd2826596ec18c8eb2"}}
