{"type":"message","id":"b372911f","parentId":"bc614cc5","timestamp":"2026-04-23T18:38:34.502Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got the project IDs. Now let me set up a helper function to create MRs and wait for merge. I'll use curl with the GitLab API.\n\nLet me now start the workflow. I need to:\n\n1. For each BE branch:\n   a. git checkout branch\n   b. git fetch + git merge develop (resolve conflicts)\n   c. Run lint (tsc / eslint if available)\n   d. git push\n   e. Create MR via GitLab API\n   f. Wait for MR to be merged\n   g. git checkout develop + git pull\n   h. Next branch\n\n\n2. For each FE branch, I'll repeat the same steps.\n\nI should consolidate some BE branches first since `fix/exam-batch-required-validation-20260423` contains multiple fixes that could be combined with `fix/course-date-validation-max-students-20260423`. Looking at what each branch actually contains, I see the first one has the overdue detection logic and venue fix, the second one has date validation and max students limit, while the third has only the course milestone notification. So I need to decide whether to merge these or keep them separate based on their actual content.\n\nNow I'm checking what linting is available for both projects.","thinkingSignature":"cf0b26167baba904f03c7751b2e268612dd10d5b42ffc0ba98d7f0f8eaffed77"},{"type":"text","text":"Có project IDs. Giờ bắt đầu workflow từng branch. Trước tiên xem lint/build commands:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dteor900597b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat package.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('scripts:', list(d.get('scripts',{}).keys()))\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dteor900597b_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat package.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('scripts:', list(d.get('scripts